title: peach custard cake
directions: Mix with a fork the first 3 ingredients until mixture looks like coarse meal.
With back of spoon, press mixture firmly onto bottom and halfway up sides of a buttered 8-inch pan.
Drain well the
peaches, saving 1/2 cup syrup . Arrange peaches on crust in pan.
Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix reserved syrup, evaporated milk and 1 egg. Pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes or until custard is firm, except in center.
(Center becomes firm on standing.)
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 9.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Prepare crabs and shrimp.
Make a paste with flour, butter and onions. Add okra and saute until brown and dry, stirring constantly.
Add all the other ingredients and hot water.
Simmer for 1 hour. Serve with cooked dry rice.

title: pork chops and rice(serves 6)
directions: Brown chops well on both sides.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt. Combine rice, raisins, onions, brown sugar, nutmeg and remaining salt in shallow casserole; mix well.
Heat water and apple juice together and pour over rice mixture.
Top with chops.
Core apple and cut into 12 wedges.
Arrange 2 wedges per chop.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in an oblong dish.
Place margarine, sugar and Cool Whip on top of potatoes.
Cook (uncovered) in a 350° oven approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Stir the mixture after 15 minutes or when the margarine, sugar and Cool Whip melts in order to coat the potatoes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix together.
Add bay leaf when rice mixture is in casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice and vegetables are cooked.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake, according to directions, in a roasting-size pan. (Note:
Use egg whites instead of whole eggs so that cake will be white rather than yellow.)
Batter will be thin, so check before cooking time is complete to see if it is done.
Cool.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Bake, covered, at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: brown bread
directions: Pour hot water over raisins.
Let set until cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's pineapple icebox pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and pineapple.
Cook until it boils; remove and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Place in cold water until cool.
Beat milk and fold into mixture; pour into a vanilla wafer pie crust.
Refrigerate to set.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, marshmallows, fruit cocktail and nuts in a large bowl.
Fold in cream.
Pour into a refrigerator tray or mold and place in refrigerator for several hours.
Serve on lettuce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all the following ingredients.
Pour into two loaf pans and bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until golden brown and tooth pick test.
Tooth pick test - insert tooth pick and if it comes out clean, bread is done.

title: fudge
directions: Butter (1) 13 X 9 X 2 inch pan OR (2) 8 X 8 inch pans. Combine sugar, milk and butter in a large pan, cook to soft ball stage. Remove from fire. Mix in the remaining ingredients until well blended. Pour into buttered pan or pans to harden.

title: beef with green peppercorn and mustard sauce
directions: In glass bowl, mash peppercorns.
Add mustard, butter, and flour.
Blend well.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead if covered and refrigerated.)
Heat oil in skillet over high heat.
Season steak with salt and pepper.
Cook to desired doneness.
5 minutes per side for rare.
Put meat aside.
Pour off drippings from the skillet.
Add broth and cream to same skillet.
Boil until sauce thickens slightly, scraping up browned bits, about 3 minutes.
Add peppercorn mixture.
Boil until sauce thickens enough to coat spoon, whisking constantly, about 1 minute.
Season sauce with salt and pepper.
Slice steak crosswise.
Arrange slices on plate. Spoon sauce over steak.

title: alice dee's famous rice
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan and add Gioia Rosa Marina.
Saute and mix constantly on low-medium heat until brown.
This will take 5 to 10 minutes.
Be careful not to burn the Rosa Marina!

title: picnic bean bake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Brown ground beef; drain off fat and set aside.
Mix brown sugar, onion soup mix and barbecue sauce.
Combine all remaining ingredients, including bacon.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be served hot or at room temperature. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Add mayonnaise and mix again.
Pile lightly in buttered casserole and sprinkle with mixture of grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: blueberry parfaits
directions: In a small bowl, combine blueberries and preserves.
In microwave, cook on High 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring twice, until blueberries are softened.
Cover; chill until ready to assemble. To serve, in each of 4 dessert or parfait glasses, layer frozen yogurt and blueberry sauce.
Garnish with almonds.
Serves 4.

title: frypan cookies
directions: Stir over low heat continuously for 3 minutes or until you feel dates are cooked.
Add 3 1/4 cups Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and dip in coconut.

title: bubble solution
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and allow to sit one hour before using.
Cover; label any leftover solution.
Store in refrigerator.
Supervise your child to keep them from tasting!

title: turkey sausage stir-fry
directions: Brown sausage in skillet. Remove from heat and drain.
In the same pan, cook vegetables until tender. Add sausage, pepper and beans. Cook about 2 minutes until warm.
Yields 6 servings.
This dish is both unusual and exciting.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: In a saucepan, combine diced onion and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and liquid.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables in saucepan; heat while stirring.
Blend sour cream and salt and add to soup mixture.
Add lima beans.
Pour mixture into a 6 cup casserole dish.
Top with crumbled Stripples and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until topping is light brown.

title: coleslaw
directions: Toss vegetables in
a
large
bowl
until evenly mixed. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly; toss gently with cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours and serve cold.

title: cajun rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix hamburger and onion mixture with tomatoes and rice.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges.

title: banana salad
directions: Slice bananas crossways and pour over lettuce, which has been broken into pieces.
Dilute salad dressing with milk.
Add sugar and pour over lettuce.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: southwest barbecue kabobs
directions: In small bowl, combine beer, steak sauce, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Pour marinade over steak.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Remove steak; reserve marinade.
Thread steak, pepper slices and onions.
In small pan, heat marinade and cornstarch to a boil.
Grill kabobs 4-inches from heat for 15 minutes or until done, turning and brushing with marinade.
Heat remaining marinade to a boil.
Serve with kabobs.

title: frosted chocolate cookies(3 dozen)
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening together.
Add sugar, milk, egg and vanilla with melted shortening.
Add to dry ingredients.
Let stand 10 minutes or more.
Drop with teaspoon on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, frost with frosting of your choice.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with toothpick and pour 1 small can (approximately 1 cup) cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool completely.
Spread 8 ounces Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle coconut over top.

title: weight watchers apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll out pie crust and place in pan. Fill with sliced apples.
In small saucepan, heat apple juice to boiling.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and stir into the hot juice.
Add cinnamon and cook until thickened.
Dot sliced apples with butter.
Pour juice over fruit.
Cover with top crust.
Bake for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake until done, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or pan, then add venison and toss on high heat until cooked.
Add vegetables and toss until tender-crisp (6 minutes).
Mix cornstarch, water, soy sauce and spices and add to pan; cook until thickened.
Top with tomato wedges and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Stir in melted butter, eggs and vanilla; beat.
Add flour, salt and walnuts; stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pasta primavera with a twist
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broccoli and carrots. Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often. Add chicken.
Heat through, stirring often. Serve over macaroni.
Toss before serving.
Serves 4.

title: asparagus and red potato salad
directions: Mix garlic, mustard, vinegar and 3/4 teaspoon salt, adding olive oil gradually.
Set aside.
Boil potatoes approximately 20 minutes.
When cool, cut into quarters.
Boil asparagus (cut into 2-inch pieces) 4 minutes.
Drain and refresh under cold water. Heat dressing until hot, then mix potatoes, scallions and asparagus.
Pour hot dressing over.
Toss and serve.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine sugar, butter and water in a saucepan.
Cook to 300° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and quickly pour onto two buttered cookie sheets. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and spread as they melt.
Sprinkle with chopped almonds.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 7 x 11 baking pan and place in a 300° oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is perfectly tender and pudding is thick and creamy, not dry.
Stir every 15 minutes with a fork, carefully turning under the brown top and scraping the edges down.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk as directed on package.
In separate bowl, cream the cream cheese with Eagle Brand milk until smooth. Add cream cheese mixture to pudding and mix well.
By hand, mix in Cool Whip, then add bananas.
Arrange wafers as desired under and around pudding.
Chill.

title: german nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and water alternately with nuts.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into the batter. Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°, then bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: easy - lazy day goulash
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole and place ingredients in dish in order listed.
Dot each layer with a little butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
To speed up baking time, cook potatoes partially before using.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Beat egg and add all other ingredients.
Mix well, then add yeast and water to mixture.
Pour in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate and use as needed.
Keep tightly covered. Makes 20 rolls.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute chicken and mushrooms in a skillet.
Use a small amount of cooking oil to prevent sticking.
Cook spaghetti noodles.
Drain noodles.
Place noodles in a large bowl.

Put in 2 tablespoons margarine or butter. Add a dash of basil, 1/2 teaspoon parsley flakes, a sprinkle of garlic and 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. You can experiment with these spices depending on your taste. Add chicken mixture to spaghetti noodles. Toss together and enjoy!

title: shell-a-roni
directions: Brown the hamburger meat and drain. Cook shell macaroni as directed and drain well. Combine hamburger meat, macaroni, tomato soup and cheese (cut in chunks) in a large soup pan.
Cook on low heat until cheese has melted. Stir frequently.
Serve hot. Serves 8 to 10.

title: deep fried catfish and hush puppies
directions: Clean and skin catfish, then cut into thick slices.
Dip slices into crackers or cornmeal, then into a mixture of egg and milk and again into the crumbs or meal.
The traditional Southern fat is lard, but vegetable oil may be used, if preferred.
The fat must be very hot.
Put the coated fish into a frying basket, immerse in the fat and cook until golden brown (do not crowd the fish, the kettle should be large and roomy).
Serve at once with Hush Puppies fried in the same fat as the fish.

title: butterscotch squares(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in morsels and nuts (optional). Spread in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: maybe mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix together both mixtures.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: fall jello salad
directions: Mix 2 cups of the cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly onto bottom of pan.
Refrigerate. Beat the cream cheese and remaining 1/2 cup sugar in bowl until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread over crust. Stir boiling water into jello.
Dissolve.
Mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into jello until slightly thickened. Remove remaining ice.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Spread remaining whipped topping over jello.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Decorate with candy pumpkins or corn.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and dice.
Mix green olives, fat-free dressing, mustard, egg and cooked potatoes.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: Cook linguine and drain.
Cook shrimp in lightly salted boiling water until pink; drain and cool.
Carefully remove from shell.
Devein shrimp, if desired.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Roll out one can crescent rolls in greased rectangular baking dish.
Press seams together.
Blend the cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk together until smooth.
Pour mixture into pan; spread evenly.
Top with second can of crescent rolls.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° until golden brown. Serve hot with fruit spread.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: The road to a friend's house is never too long.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Add milk and vanilla. Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Put soda in hot water.
Bake at 400°.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides with oil in 12-inch skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Put margarine in a 2-quart microwavable dish.
Microwave full power 20 to 30 seconds until melted.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, chicken bouillon and water.
Microwave full power 3 to 5 minutes, stirring twice until mixture boils.
Place potatoes in bottom of lightly greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Arrange onion on top of potatoes.
Pour chicken broth mixture evenly over top.
Arrange browned pork chops over top of potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue baking 30 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: holiday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt or angle food cake pan. Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Add next four ingredients.
Bake 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked spinach with raisins
directions: In a small bowl, let the raisins soak in hot water for 30 minutes or until they are plump.
Drain.
In another bowl, combine well the eggs, cream cheese, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and stir in the spinach, the raisins, the half and half, the Jack cheese and the vinegar.
Transfer the mixture to a buttered 9-inch glass pie plate and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until it is set and puffed slightly.
Cool for 2 to 3 minutes before serving, noting that pie will collapse a bit.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southern banana cake
directions: Line pan with cookies, sides and bottom. Put in some of the pudding. Then layer sliced bananas, all 4 or 6. Add the rest of the pudding. Spread in a layer. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Refrigerate for 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: soft ginger cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Rub together and add spices and lemon, eggs, then molasses, 1/2 cup soda and water.
Stir quickly and add sifted flour last.
Bake in greased pan in 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jumbo oatmeal raisin peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Add peanut butter.
Put aside.
Mix sugar, brown sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower.
Grate eggs.
Mix with everything. Refrigerate until served.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Place marshmallows and pecans in large mixing bowl.
Melt chips; add milk and blend thoroughly.
Do get to hot.
Pour over marshmallows and pecans.
Mix and drop on waxed paper with any size spoon.
Makes 60 to 80 pieces.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir in Chex and put in a large plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Shake to coat.
Store in covered container.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven until done, no longer than 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add whole corn, creamed corn and corn bread mix.
Gently mix with fork.
Add eggs and mix with fork.
Drop sour cream by tablespoons in different areas on top of corn mixture.
Fold in gently.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes until mixture is firm.
Cool slightly before cutting into squares. Yields 12 servings.

title: apricot glazed pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour; measure and add dry ingredients to flour.
Combine sour cream and flavorings.
Beginning with flour and ending with flour, add alternately with sour cream mixture.
Pour into a well-greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and gradually pour glaze over cake.

title: summer crab spread
directions: Cream lemon juice, minced onion and cream cheese.
Spread on bottom of 8 x 8-inch dish.
Flake crab on top of cream cheese, covering completely.
Spread cocktail sauce over crab.
Sprinkle with fresh, chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers.
(Pepperidge Farm hearty wheat go well.)

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix together and pour in a gallon Ziploc bag.
Add 1 pound of cut up or boneless chicken.
Marinate several hours or all day. Grill or broil.
This is a recipe by Doc Holliday.

title: hamburger pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and let soak 2 to 3 hours. Make brine
of
sugar,
water, vinegar and turmeric.
Squeeze cucumbers and put in solution.
Just bring to a boil then put into jars and seal.

title: play dough
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan and cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Stir all the time.
Let cool and knead in hands.
Keep in covered container.

title: delicious pot roast
directions: Score roast in several places; fill each score with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Sear roast well on all sides in oil. Remove from pan; drain excess fat from roast and return roast to pan.
Mix Coke and catsup together and pour over roast.
Cover and bake for 3 hours at 325°.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Line greased casserole dish with tortillas which have been soaked in broth. Add chicken. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken, reserving some of the cheese to sprinkle on top. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes. Makes a large casserole. Freezes well.

title: potluck meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Brown in skillet or microwave.
Prepare sauce and pour over top.
Keep warm until ready to serve.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix dry ingredients with cooking oil.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Marinate chicken, steaks or any kind of meat.
Mix with green peppers, mushrooms, squash and onions for shish kabobs. Marinate 3 to 24 hours.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: taco salad
directions: Drain hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together.
Crunch up corn chips in bag before opening.
Add chips.
Add dressing.
Mix well and serve.

title: chinese salad
directions: Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Good for several days.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze the juice from 1 lemon into a large glass.
Add sugar and cold water.
Stir until mixed.
Add ice cubes and enjoy!

title: white cap fruit mold
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail, reserving syrup.
Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Add the reserved syrup and enough water to measure 1 3/4 cups.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit cocktail.
Pour into a 9-inch dish. Chill until firm. Unmold. Combine the heavy cream, Miracle Whip and marshmallows. Spoon over jello.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: root beer(quick method)
directions: Now add enough water for
one
gallon.	Set
in the sun for about 3 hours or more.
If	you
want
more
zip let stand longer. Store in refrigerator.

title: cream of wheat corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into hot skillet, greased with 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons bacon fat or shortening.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: beef enchiladas with cheese
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, crumble meat.
Cook by microwave 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain fat.
Add 1 cup cheese and olives to meat.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, blend tomato paste with enchilada sauce mix.
Stir in water.
Cover and cook by microwave for 8 minutes.
Pour 1 cup prepared enchilada sauce in 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dip each tortilla into remaining heated sauce.
Spoon beef mixture in center of each tortilla.
Fold sides of tortilla over filling and place in baking dish, seam side down. Pour remaining sauce over the top.
Then top with 1 1/2 cups cheese; cover with plastic wrap.
Heat by microwave for 3 minutes. Makes 8 enchiladas.

title: posse stew
directions: In a skillet, brown ground meat and onion; drain. Stir in tomatoes, beans, chillies, hominy and corn.
Season with salt and pepper.
For a thicker stew, combine cornstarch and water, then stir into stew.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: southside cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press hole in center of each cookie with thumb.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Fill while warm.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add other ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash delight
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Slice squash.
Chop onion and add to ground beef.
Mix eggs, milk and flour well.
Pour over all and simmer until done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pinch together the crescent rolls to form a pizza base; bake to brown.
Whip together cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Italian dry dressing.
Top with broccoli, cauliflower, shredded carrots, cheese, tomatoes, etc.

title: german potato salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Remove from heat and blend in flour, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and blend in mayonnaise.
Reserve 1/4 cup sauce.
Fold in beans, potatoes, franks and onions.
Spoon into casserole dish and add the reserved sauce to the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oriental green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving some chow mein noodles. Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top during last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and put in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend.
Pour in glass and drink.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Put in a freezer container.
Add milk to fill line.
Freeze.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
press graham cracker crumbs evenly over bottom of pan.
Spread chocolate chips on top of graham crackers.
Spread coconut over chocolate chips. Spread chopped nuts over coconut.
Pour condensed milk over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: butterscotch apple salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip, apples, marshmallows and peanuts.
Let set 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: mints
directions: Mash cream cheese.
Add flavoring and coloring.
Mix in sugar. Finally, knead with hands until like pie dough.
Roll into marble size balls and dip in granulated sugar.
Press sugared side into candy mold and unmold onto wax paper.
Makes 25 roses and 25 leaves.

title: tuna ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, together in a mixing bowl.
Thoroughly mix and roll into ball.
Chill overnight to make ball firm.
Remove and roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: donna's buttery biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in milk all at once.
Round up into a ball and place on floured surface.
Roll out or pat until 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into rounds or squares.
Spread top with soft butter.
Bake at 425° in ungreased pan for 12 minutes or until bottom is browned.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine biscuit mix, the first 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill greased muffin pans two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly and remove from pans.
Mix the second 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Dip muffin tops in melted butter, then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: breakfast caramel cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients, reserving a cup of cake mix. Pour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix last four ingredients into a mixture that you are able to crumble over the cake mixture and fold in with a knife (a marbleized effect).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fork comes out clean.

title: tropical delight salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil butter, both sugars, corn syrup and salt for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla. Pour over popped corn, stirring well.
A long shallow pan works best.
Bake at 225° or 250° for approximately 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Mix artichokes, mayonnaise, cheese and garlic salt.
Pour into ungreased casserole (flat pie pan type).
Sprinkle more Parmesan cheese on top.
Top with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Delicious served with most any cracker.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until browned. Remove fat.
Add soup, water, vegetables, tomatoes and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer 2 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in rice.
Remove from heat. Cover. Let stand 5 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Recipe can be prepared ahead of time and rewarmed when ready to serve.
Baked or unbaked balls can be frozen.

title: coffee squares
directions: Put first 4 ingredients plus vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and cook until thick (about 20 minutes).
Cool overnight. Add to a small container of Cool Whip.
Dip with pieces of fruit.

title: zucchini stew
directions: In large skillet heat oil, onion, tomatoes, celery leaves and basil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in cooked beans and carrots for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chestnut-mushroom stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir the onion, chestnuts and mushrooms in butter. Cook until onion is tender. Add this to 1/3 of the bread cubes.
In a very large bowl, mix this and all other ingredients.
Toss!
Stuff turkey just before roasting.
Makes 5 quarts; enough for a 20 to 24 pound turkey.

title: e-z layer dessert
directions: Crust:
Chop pecan pieces in blender.
Combine flour, butter and pecan chips to make the crust.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa. Add margarine, water and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat again.
Bake in 2 layer pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° until done.

title: zucchini dip
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Beau Monde until smooth.
Stir in walnuts and zucchini carefully. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: no cook ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until thick (about 2 minutes). Strain as your pour into freezer and add balance of ingredients.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 12-inch slightly greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix the next 4 ingredients and spread over pretzel crust.
Chill.
Mix jello and water.
Add strawberries.
When thickened, pour over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: easy dressing
directions: Bring first ingredients to boil in large soup pan.
Take from heat; stir in eggs and croutons.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma pruett's buttermilk candy
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk and syrup to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter, soda and peanut butter.
Beat until smooth and begins to thicken.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onions.
Heat 1 gallon of water in large pan.
When water is hot, add carrots, potatoes, corn with water in can, and peas with water in can.
Continue cooking.
Add hamburger mixture to vegetable mixture.
Cook thoroughly.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, except use pineapple in place of water.
Stir shredded coconut and rum flavoring into batter.
Pour into two greased 8-inch round cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° according to package.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping and toasted coconut or frost as desired.

title: baked sea bass with spinach
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In bowl, toss juice, 1 teaspoon zest and sea bass fillets together.
Marinate 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, toss together baby spinach, sliced mushrooms and olive oil.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Place fish fillets on top of spinach mixture.
Cover dish; bake 10 minutes.
Uncover; bake 5 minutes more or until fish is flaky and opaque.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turnip greens and corn dumplings
directions: Just before turnip greens finish cooking, make corn dumplings. Roll into balls and drop on top of greens and cook 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together well.
Fold in the whipped topping and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.
Cut into squares for serving on a leaf of crisp lettuce.

title: creamy broccoli
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put into bottom of a shallow baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry and mushrooms.
Pour over broccoli and cover with bread crumbs. Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; gradually add eggs, milk and vanilla. Cream well.
Then add flour and baking powder, sifted together. Chill for 10 minutes.
Roll and cut into desired shape.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: lemon yogurt fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool. Add yogurt and fruit and pour into mold.
Chill.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a double boiler, add the following ingredients: butter, powdered sugar, semi-sweet chocolate chips and evaporated milk. Cook until smooth.
Remove from stove.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and/or 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Best when served warm.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, butter and wine in a bowl.
In a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, place the raw rice.
Mix 1/2 soup mixture with the rice.
Place chicken on top of the rice.
Pour rest of soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours, covered with foil.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine gelatin and water and let gelatin soften.
Add sugar to scalded milk; add rice and then add egg and cook until egg is cooked.
Add all of this to softened gelatin with salt and vanilla.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, stirring until dissolved.
Chill in refrigerator and add whipped cream.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with whipped cream and cherry on top.

title: tamales
directions: Layer in baking dish.
Bake until heated.

title: orange slice fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternating.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Bake in well greased angel food pan for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: ro-tel dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer until soft and smooth.
Add tomatoes, slowly mixing with fork. (I didn't use all the juice.) Add onions to mixture. Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serve with large corn chips.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Combine crabmeat, mayonnaise, horseradish and hot sauce. Spread into greased shallow baking dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: clammed up party rye
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients with enough mayonnaise to make it stick together.
Spread on party rye and broil until cheese melts.

title: broccoli with sauce(for those who don't like broccoli)
directions: Cook broccoli (boil in water for 10 to 12 minutes).
Mix soy sauce, Canola oil, vinegar and sugar.
Heat sauce mixture and bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over drained broccoli.
Serve hot.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Then mix all together.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese melts on top.

title: jack robinson meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients. Shape and bake in oven at 350° about 1 hour.

title: orange delight
directions: Prepare jello substituting juice for water.
Fold in ice cream until melted.
Add mandarin oranges.

title: busy-day chowder
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
In a large Dutch oven, combine hamburger and remaining ingredients.
Simmer gently until ingredients come to a boil.
Low salt soups and vegetables can be substituted.
Can also be done in a slow-cooker so flavors blend slowly.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain, saving enough drippings to saute onion.
In a saucepan, mix all ingredients together and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Roll out pastry to fit a 9-inch pie plate.
Flute edges; prick bottom.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 8 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, oats, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into meatballs and cook until done.
(Do very well in the microwave.)
Drain off grease.
Mix together catsup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, sugar and water; simmer while meatballs are cooking.
Pour sauce over meatballs and simmer until ready to serve.

title: german breaded pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops and remove bones.
Mix egg with onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip chops in mixture, then in bread crumbs, coating them well.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute chops over low heat.
Turn over until browned on both sides and cooked through.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown ground beef.
Add salt, garlic salt, pepper and tomato sauce to browned beef.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and chopped onions.
Add noodles; mix well. Alternate layers of beef and noodle mixtures.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: easy peach crisp pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat egg.
Add cream and pie filling.
Spread in pie shell.
Blend sugar, flour and oleo; sprinkle over peach mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue to bake another 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and salt and pepper.
Put in greased pie plate.
Add Cheddar cheese and tomatoes.
Blend 3 eggs, milk and Bisquick in blender for 1 minute.
Then pour over hamburger mixture.
Bake at 450° until inserted knife comes out clean, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot pena sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients until garlic bubbles a couple of minutes. Add 1 large can crushed tomatoes and 1 can peeled tomatoes.
Cook at least 45 minutes.

title: texas torte
directions: To eggs; add flour, salt, milk, chilies and cheese; beat well. Pour into a flat, well greased 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and cut into tiny squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine cream and sugar and put on medium heat.
Stirring constantly, let it come to a boil and boil until when tested in cold water it comes to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add other 3 ingredients.
Stir until starts to thicken, then pour into greased plate.

title: french fry casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Layer
meat and French fries in a baking dish.
Mix Velveeta, soup and tomatoes in saucepan and heat until
cheese
melts.
Pour
over meat and French fries. Add water
until covered.
Cook, covered with foil, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until fries are tender.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy iced coffee(serves 3)
directions: Blend milk, water, Espresso powder and brandy in blender. With machine running, gradually add the ice cubes and process until smooth.
Pour over ice in goblets.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: tempura batter
directions: Mix together cornstarch, flour, seasoned salt and paprika. Add egg and water.
Beat until smooth.
Dip fresh cucumbers or yellow squash in batter and fry in hot oil.
Eat while hot.

title: raspberry chicken breasts(microwave)
directions: Arrange chicken breast halves with thickest part to the outside edge in a square dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle with ginger root.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, rotating dish half turn after 4 minutes.
Mix preserves and vinegar in 1-cup measure.
Microwave 30 to 60 seconds, or until warm.
Serve over chicken.
Serve with rice pilaf and fresh raspberries as garnish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add wet ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Cool and slice.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg.
Beat well. Sift flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt together.
Add molasses to creamed mixture.
Alternately add coffee and soda mixture with dry ingredients.
Raisins or nutmeats may be added, if desired.

title: summer buffet salad
directions: Cut lettuce in wedges and arrange other vegetables around the lettuce so that each person may have a complete serving and help himself to the salad dressing.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan; stir in flour and nuts until mixed.
Press evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Combine 2 packages instant pudding with 3 cups milk; pour over cheese mixture.
Let set.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Place 1 layer of potatoes, then sprinkle rice over them, then a layer of raw ground beef.
Repeat another layer of the 3 ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover entire casserole with canned tomatoes (not whole) and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: avocado pie
directions: Combine milk, avocado and lemonade.
Turn into whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: penuche candy
directions: Grease a small pan, approximately 4 x 8-inch.

title: potato soup
directions: In soup pot, saute celery and onion.
Add potatoes and carrot. Just cover with water and boil until potatoes are tender.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spoon on cherry pie filling; pour dry cake mix over top.
Slice margarine into small pieces; arrange on top.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stardust salad
directions: Mix both boxes of Jell-O with hot water and add 1 1/2 cups of cold water.
Add bananas and pineapple.
Cover top with miniature marshmallows.
Let congeal.
Mix sugar, flour, pineapple juice and 1 beaten egg until foamy.
Cook until thick and let cool.
Pour over top of congealed Jell-O.
Whip the whipping cream and combine with cream cheese and pour over other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: diego bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add Crisco and sugar.
Let cool.
Add yeast, eggs and 3 cups of flour.
Set aside.
Let rise until double.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a double boiler until thick. Cool.
Cream the cream cheese in large mixing bowl.
Add cooled mix.
Add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in half bag of marshmallows.
Chill for about 1/2 an hour and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a LARGE bowl by hand.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before moving to cooling rack.
Yield:
7 to 8 dozen.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Melt butter.
Saute mushrooms, parsley, onions and thyme.
Add softened bread crumbs to this and enough water to moisten bread. Set this aside.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups milk until tender, stir occasionally.
When rice is tender add margarine, beaten eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and 2 more cups of milk.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: halloween makeup
directions: Mix Crisco and cornstarch together; add food coloring for desired color.
Use tissue, soap and water to clean off makeup. Will keep for about a month in closed jar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: holiday rum balls
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 cup of the confectioners sugar, pecans and cocoa.
Stir in rum and corn syrup.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in remaining sugar.
Store in tightly covered container. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Cream together butter, fruit powder and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough overnight. Roll into balls and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
The balls puff slightly and become very light and airy when they bake.

title: herbed mushrooms
directions: Trim mushroom stems flush with caps; save scraps for other uses.
Melt butter in a frying pan over medium heat; add onion and mushrooms.
Cook until most of the juices have evaporated.
Add basil, oregano, thyme, garlic salt, hot pepper seasoning, lime juice and sherry.
(If made ahead, cover and chill as long as 2 days.)
Just before serving, cook over medium-high heat, stirring, until mushrooms are hot.
Keep warm over canned heat or alcohol burner.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen appetizers.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together, adding corn bread mix last. Pour into a greased glass baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In bowl, combine chocolate, pecans, eggs, vanilla, flour and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes at 300°.
Yields 18 slices.
Each serving equals: 1 fat; 1 bread and 1/2 fruit.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat eggs.
Bone chicken breasts that have already been cooked.
Dip in eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in oil. Arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seaweed soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add chopped vegetables, water, herbs and seaweed (cut into small pieces) and cook until tender.
Stir in lentils and miso.
Enjoy!

title: grilled stuffed franks
directions: Cut frankfurters lengthwise, almost through, but not quite, and spread cut sides with mustard.
Slice cheese and pickles into long strips and lay a strip of each in the franks.
Wrap a slice of bacon around in a spiral fashion, fastening the ends with toothpicks.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well the corn, biscuit mix, egg, salad oil and milk. Spread half of mixture in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Cover with green chile peppers (drained) and cheese (sliced).
Spread remaining batter over top.

title: cantonese soup
directions: In large saucepan, lightly brown pork in oil, stirring frequently.
Stir in soy sauce, pepper and ginger.
Cook 5 minutes. Add chicken broth; simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Garnish each serving with noodles.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Cream the butter, egg and sugar together.
Add milk and flour. Mix all together.
Makes a thick mixture.
Leave in refrigerator overnight, then roll out dough and cut out cookie shapes. Sprinkle with nonpareils and bake in oven at 300°.
Watch carefully; do not burn.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Place ingredients in bread pan in order listed.
Use dough setting; press start.
When setting is complete, remove dough from bread pan.
Place on lightly floured surface.
Divide dough into 24 pieces.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased baking sheet(s) about 1/2-inch apart.
Let stand, covered, in a warm draft-free place 30 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. You may add to cake mix such things as raisins, nuts, coconut, chocolate chips, etc.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bacon-horseradish dip
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble and save back just a little for garnish.
In medium bowl, mix soup mix, sour cream, crumbled bacon, horseradish and mustard; mix all together thoroughly. Cover; chill 2 hours.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring the brown sugar and melted butter to a boil.
Add the milk
and
boil.
Take off and add the confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Stir.
Spread on cake while icing is hot.
If it gets hard, put in a small amount of warm water.

title: s. p. jerky
directions: Save half of mix and set aside.
Rub 1/2 on meat.
Refrigerate 3 days.
Remove and rub on other half of saved mixture.
Dry at room temperature for approximately 3 days.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Mix well flour, butter or margarine, pecans, sugar and salt and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Mix well cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Blend pudding and milk.
Spread on mix. Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Serves 16.

title: mocha truffles
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips.
Add cream cheese, coffee and water; mix well.
Chill until firm enough to work.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper.
Freeze about 30 minutes or chill in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Melt chocolate coating in microwave in a flat pan.
Dip balls and place on waxed paper to harden.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: peach or strawberry turnovers
directions: Mix well with fork.
Form in ball and roll out on pastry sheet.
Use cookie cutter or glass and cut.
Spread thin layer of preserves on dough.
Fold in half and press with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until golden brown.

title: beans and gravy
directions: Saute bacon in saucepan until almost crisp.
Add the onion; continue cooking until the bacon is done and the onion is a nice tender, golden brown.
Add the flour; blend well.
Stir in the mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Last, add the string beans. Simmer for a few minutes to heat through, stirring until smooth. Serves 4.

title: pancake tart with jam and banana
directions: Whip the eggs; add the flour, salt and half of the milk and whip until thick and even.
Whip the remaining milk together with the melted cooled butter and add to mixture.
Heat the pan and butter it.
Pour a little dough into the pan and bake thin crisp pancakes.
Sandwich with a layer of jam and thinly sliced bananas between each layer of pancake.
Serve the pancake tart warm with slightly whipped cream or soft vanilla ice cream.

title: pasta salad
directions: Slice tomatoes, onion, green onions, red bell pepper, green bell pepper and cucumbers.
Mix with cooked spiral noodles.
Pour dressing over salad.

title: strawberry jubilee
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces and put 1/2 into bottom of glass dish.
Dissolve jello in one cup of hot water.
Let congeal slightly.
Add sweetened strawberries (sweetened with 1 cup sugar) to jello and spread over cake.
Put another layer of cake in dish.
Prepare instant pudding mix using 2 cups of cold milk and spread over cake.
Cover pudding layer with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: aunt vi's grape-nut custard
directions: Combine Grape-Nuts and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a slight boil.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla in Corning dish until smooth. Mix with warm Grape-Nuts and milk.
Bake in pan of hot water for 1 hour at 350° until a silver knife inserted comes out clean.

title: beef jerkey
directions: Slice beef real thin.
Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Add enough to meet your taste.
There is no certain amount of one thing.
Let beef set in liquid overnight.
Lay flat on cookie sheet; let dry in a warm oven overnight or if it is cold weather, hang beef in front of a wood burning stove for 1 or 2 days.
You will love it.
You can use deer if you like, too.

title: net's potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and half of cheese in large pot and heat through until bubbly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil to prevent burning.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: poor man's persimmon pudding
directions: Mix
persimmon	pulp,
sugar, flour and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well and pour into greased pudding pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: 5 flavor cake
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into a prepared 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.
Add a glaze.

title: banana bread without milk or eggs
directions: Mix together and put in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes or until done.

title: creole shrimp saute
directions: Cook celery, pepper, mushrooms, onion and garlic in butter and oil in large skillet.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, thyme, salt, red pepper flakes and okra.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and boil 5 minutes or until okra is tender.
Stir in shrimp and cook additional 5 minutes or until shrimp just turns pink.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: two-step pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Cover and simmer until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given while cold.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Place in baked pie shell and use the egg whites for meringue, with 8 tablespoons sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pour ketchup down middle of loaf and add Worcestershire sauce.
Spread over top and sides.

title: spread delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve as spread on cucumber slice, carrot rounds, crackers or toast.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spoon bread
directions: If using self-rising meal, omit baking powder and salt.

title: smothered burgers
directions: Mix ingredients except beef. Add beef and mix thoroughly. Shape into 7 burgers.

title: fluff salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in cherry juice over low heat in a saucepan. Add to marshmallow mixture the cream cheese and blend.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Mold and chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar. Add peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Drizzle Hershey's syrup and pecans on top. Then chill in refrigerator.

title: party cheese wreath
directions: Beat cheddar cheese and cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add rest of ingredients, except garnish, and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours, or overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine eggs, onion, soup and mayonnaise. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer broccoli, Cheddar cheese and sauce.
Top with croutons or cracker crumbs with margarine sprinkled over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fried liver and bacon
directions: Remove rind from bacon strips.
Place in frying pan and cook quickly, turning frequently.
Cook until the fat is clear.
Lift onto a hot dish and keep hot.
Cut liver into slices (1/2-inch thick) and coat with seasoned flour.
Fry liver on pan, in bacon fat.
Fry quickly on both sides (1 to 2 minutes).
Lift onto a hot dish and serve with fried bacon strips.
Garnish with parsley.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat.
Return meat to skillet and add oregano, cumin, seasoned salt, garlic powder, paprika and taco seasoning mix.
Stir in refried beans and continue to stir until heated through.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape and roll into a ball.
Roll the cheese ball in the pecans.
Serve at room temperature.
May be frozen.
Makes about one 4-inch cheese ball.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix with rice.
Add soups and mix thoroughly. Salt and pepper chicken pieces and place on top of rice and soup mixture which you have put in a large, flat baking dish.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip the Dream Whip; set aside.
Put pineapple and cranberry sauce in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; fold into Dream Whip.
Put in an 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 11-inch dish and freeze.
Take out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: candy bonbons
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl with hands.
Refrigerate until cold.
Shape into small balls (not more than 3/4-inch). Refrigerate again.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler pan.
Dip balls using a toothpick into chocolate.
Makes approximately 27 dozen balls.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve all in nonmetal pitcher or bowl; chill.
Just before serving add 1 (28 ounce) bottle club soda, chilled.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil and debone the chicken.
Reserve broth for boiling spaghetti.
Saute onion and bell pepper in 1/2 stick margarine. Mix the cooked noodles, onion and bell pepper and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Add chicken, peas and mushrooms; mix again.
Top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.
(I do not drain the noodles, but dip them from the pan; this leaves them moist.) Some broth may be added before adding the cheese to prevent drying out during baking.
This makes a large meal.

title: mary's pumpkin cake
directions: Blend together eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: fish stew from zaire
directions: Place the corned beef in a large soup pot or stockpot with enough water to cover completely.
Bring to a boil over high heat. As soon as the water boils, pour it off and add fresh water to cover the corned beef.
Add the bay leaf, peppercorns, garlic, celery and the halved carrots.

Bring the water back to a boil over high heat, skimming any foam that rises to the surface. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover and simmer, skim as necessary, until the meat is tender but still firm, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: sara's jello dessert
directions: Step 1:
Put each flavor jello following in individual 8-inch pans.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
After jelled, cut into 1-inch cubes.

title: viennese hamburger
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, milk and salt.
Mix well. Shape into 24 balls.
Cook onion in 1/4 cup butter or margarine until lightly browned and tender. Remove from pan. Add meat balls, brown on all sides and remove from pan.
Stir flour into drippings in pan. Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add to pan. Return onion to pan. Add tomato paste.
Mix.
Stir gently over low heat until thickened.
Return meat balls to pan. Simmer gently 20 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix ingredients, quick and easy.
Refrigerate, will keep up to two weeks (serves 4 or 5, recommend doubling).

title: friendship tea
directions: Use 2 scant teaspoons of dry tea mixture to a cup of hot water!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Do not rinse.
Mix vegetables.
Prepare dressing.
Pour over all mixed vegetables.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crab quiche
directions: Line 9-inch quiche pan with pastry and trim off excess edge of pan.
Place a piece of aluminum foil (buttered side down over pastry).
Gently press into pastry shell.
This will keep the sides of shell from collapsing.
Cover foil with a layer of dried beans or peas.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove foil and peas.
Prick shell and bake 3 to 5 minutes more or until slightly brown.
Cool.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, soda and salt; add remaining ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into a greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 10 servings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix in cheeses and spices.
Set aside.
Prepare hot roll mix according to directions on box, allowing to rise only once.
Divide dough into 2 equal pieces. Roll out dough into two 8 x 10-inch squares.
Spoon half of sausage mixture onto each piece of dough.
Roll closed.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook the vegetables in the oil until tender.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 20 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: rich yellow cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter until creamy.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour, salt and baking powder mixture alternating with milk.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Garnish or frost with your favorite frosting or filling.
Enjoy.

title: catfish stew
directions: Dice salt pork (3/8-inch).
Fry or microwave until crisp, don't drain.
Dice potatoes and onions (1/2 inch).
In large pot place onions, potatoes, cooked salt pork, red pepper, black pepper and enough water just to top of mixture.
Simmer until potatoes are done.
Dice catfish (3/4 inch).
Add and bring to boil.
Turn to low heat.
Add tomato paste.
Salt to taste.
Bring to simmer. Stew is done.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts.

title: triplet cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and eggs thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Divide into 3 equal portions for variations.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place crushed saltines on top and pat with butter.
Cook at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: shoo-fly-pie
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and sugar.
Put aside a little of this crumb mix for top of pie.
Combine molasses and water; add baking soda. Combine dry ingredients and liquid mixture.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake in 325° oven about 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in oil.
Put into an 8-quart pan. Add potatoes, ham and water (4-quarts).
You can use chicken broth if you like.
Boil until potatoes and carrots are soft.
Add half and half. Turn to medium heat.
Chunk up cheese and add; stir until cheese is melted.
If soup is not thick enough, thicken with instant mashed potatoes.

title: fresh berry pie filling
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to boil in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add jello (dry).
Stir in berries.
Pour into 9-inch pastry crust.
Refrigerate.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Combine butter and spices; mix well.
Place tenderloin in a roasting pan on a rack.
Brush with mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes for rare.
Slice.
Serve with cold sour cream and horseradish.

title: oatmeal candy (no bake)
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine together and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Drop onto wax paper to cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple, stir in the pudding, marshmallows, nuts and cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with cheese and nuts.

title: melinda's rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add rice. Dump contents of 3 cans into casserole (do not dilute soup) and stir.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 cups of cooked rice.
Doubles or triples easily for larger groups.

title: punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.

title: lemon frappe
directions: Combine first three ingredients in container of an electric blender, process until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides. Spoon into a pitcher; stir in ginger ale.
Serve immediately. Makes 5 cups.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Mix crumbs, milk, salt, onion and curry powder.
Add beef and blend thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 36 (1-inch) balls.
Arrange balls in a double circle on a round microwave plate.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until done.
Rotate dish every 2 minutes.
Repeat procedure with remaining meatballs.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Alternate layers of croutons, salmon and cheese (2 layers of each) in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix 2 cups milk with eggs, Worcestershire sauce, salt and dry mustard powder.
Pour over other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: big appetite pancakes
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Add dry ingredients and oil; mix well. Spoon batter onto hot greased griddles and brown on both sides. Makes 85 servings.

title: choco-caramel cookies
directions: Beat sugar, butter, egg yolk, milk and vanilla until blended. Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Blend into shortening mixture.
Chill dough at least 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Beat egg whites slightly.
Shape dough into 1-inch ball. Dip each ball into egg white and roll in nuts.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb gently in center of each ball.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
While cookies bake prepare caramel filling.
Press center of each cookie again with thumb to make indentation.
Immediately spoon about 1/2 teaspoon caramel filling in center of each cookie.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Drizzle chocolate mixture over top of cookies.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add egg right before you dress the salad.
Prepare lettuce by washing and tearing into bite size pieces.
Toss in cheese and croutons.
Add oil mixture.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cook beef and dried onions in water until tender.
Pull meat apart with fork.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes or until cooked down.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add juices.
Great for a party.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Add onion, parsley, optional ingredients, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well; form into balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: coke salad
directions: Strain juice from fruits into cup.
Add water to make 2 cups liquid; heat.
Pour over jello; stir until dissolved.
Add Coke. Chill until thickened a little.
Add fruit and pecans.
Return to refrigerator.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: tropical glazed yams
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 25 minutes.
Let cool to touch; peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices so edges overlap in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Drain pineapple; set aside.
Combine pineapple syrup, sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, orange rind and apricot in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Add butter, pecans and pineapple; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot salad with cumin
directions: Toss all ingredients in medium size bowl.
Serve within 1 hour.

title: melon magic
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and cover.
Run on liquefy until smooth.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel, devein and wash shrimp; set aside.
(If shrimp are frozen, let thaw first in the refrigerator.)
Simmer tomato sauce, onion, celery, green pepper, mushrooms, parsley and pepper in skillet for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 10 to 15 minutes more, until shrimp are tender.
Serve over brown rice.
Serves 2.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix well; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stella henson's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Make batter of scant cup self-rising flour, egg, sugar and 1/2 cup fruit juice.
Add melted butter.
Pour this batter into bottom of baking dish.
Have fruit boiling hot (add sugar to fruit according to need and kind of fruit when heating). Spoon fruit on batter.
Slowly pour on about 1 cup of juice from fruit over heated fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples and cut in eighths.
Arrange in pie shell. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Combine 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and butter.
Blend.
Fold in whipped cream until well blended. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 4 or 5 hours.
Drizzle top with hot fudge before serving.
Good!!

title: kenna kay's sugar cream pie(in honor of stallion, "cut across")
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, cinnamon, vanilla and whole milk; mix thoroughly.
Add Milnot and stir; mix in flour and stir until free of any lumps.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to first mixture and mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Reduce heat and finish baking at 350°.

title: no-fuss pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place in baking dish.
Mix applesauce, soy sauce and onion powder and spoon over chops. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter-chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup in a large pot.
Cook over moderate heat.
Stir frequently until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Stir until well blended.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels together over hot water.
Stir until well blended.
Spread evenly over rice mixture.
Cool until firm.
Slice into squares.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 2-quart casserole, beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and pineapple.
Mix well.
Cover with bread crumbs. Dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes or covered for 45 minutes.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter well.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add flour gradually.
Add flavorings.
Fold in 7-Up with spoon.
Do not beat in 7-Up.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° and then test for doneness.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer each ingredient as listed.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: margie's dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
If too thick, thin with a little milk.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 1 minute.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan.
Pour mixture in loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: peppermint crunch bark
directions: Melt white chocolate for 1 minute in microwave.
Stir in peppermint.
Spread on cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Place in freezer until cool (approximately 3 minutes); break into pieces.

title: mom-mom jones' corn pudding
directions: Melt butter and add to creamed corn.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt. Blend well and add to corn.
Add canned milk and beaten eggs. After blended, pour into greased casserole and bake at 300°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: cheese bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Add sugar.
Pour over cake mixture. Sprinkle with chopped nuts or coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mediterranean loaf
directions: Cut off ends from the bread.
Using a long handled kitchen fork, scoop out enough bread dough to make a long hollow tube with a 1/2 inch crust, reserving the bread crumbs.
In a large mixing bowl combine the bread crumbs with the tomatoes, scallions, olives, parsley, cheese, thyme, oregano.
Gently but thoroughly mix.
Add the olive oil, white wine, and salt and pepper. Thoroughly mix again.
Holding one end of the tube of sourdough bread closed with the palm of your hand, stuff the hollow bread with the tomato mixture, being sure to pack firmly.
Wrap the stuffed loaf with aluminum foil and chill for 24 hours.

title: savory rice blend
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash and drain wild rice.
Saute wild rice, celery and onion in margarine.
Pour into greased casserole. Pour broth over rice. Stir in seasonings and mushrooms.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Add regular rice, cover and cook 45 minutes more or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: seasoned oven fries
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into thirds. Then cut each portion into thirds. In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the butter, oil and seasoned salt. Add potatoes; shake to coat. Place in single layer on a greased baking sheet. Bake uncovered at 450 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender, turning once. Yield 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: For crust, bake rolls flat in 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let get very cool.

title: barbecue brisket marinade
directions: Mix all together.
Rub into 5 to 7 pound brisket.
Leave at room temperature 1 to 2 hours to marinate.
Cook on grill until done.

title: mexican-vegetable soup
directions: Wash kale and strip leaves from stalk (do not use heavy stalk).
Peel and chop potatoes.
Add with kale to a pot, along with broth and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer.
While simmering, chop chorizo and brown in its own fat. If chorizo is soft, remove it from its casing.
When chorizo is cooked, remove from skillet with a slotted spoon and add to soup pot.
Add onion, pepper, carrot, garlic, cilantro and tomatoes to soup.
Simmer until vegetables are tender and tomatoes have blended.
Stir in corn; season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: greek stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Combine with the next 4 ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bavarian sausage fry
directions: Brown onions and hot sausage in oil.
Add sauerkraut, sliced apples and raisins.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve sausages whole or slice into pieces.

title: beef and bean burrito
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Drain salsa; reserve liquid. Add seasoning mix, beans, chilies and liquid from salsa.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Prepare flour tortillas.
Top with lettuce and cheese and 1 tablespoon of salsa.
Fold edge of tortillas over to cover filling.
Fold envelope style and roll.
Serves 10.

title: paula's pork chops
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain fat.
Brown pork chops with seasoned salt. Pour milk and simmer.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Simmer for at least one hour before adding cornstarch.

title: white fruit salad
directions: Add vinegar to beaten eggs and sugar.
Cook until thick, turn on low and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add gelatin softened in cold water.
Add crushed pineapple, fruit cocktail, nuts and whipped cream and chill.

title: potatoes anna
directions: In microwave, melt butter with salt.
Preheat oven to 425°. With knife, slice potatoes and onions about 1/4-inch thick.
In greased 8-inch pie plate, arrange potato and onion slices, overlapping them.
Drizzle butter mixture on top.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans; pat into well greased 9 X 13 dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Spread on top of crust. (Save some.) Mix pudding with milk. Pour on top. Cover with remaining Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: sweet peppers
directions: Mix together.
Bring to a boil.
Wash and slice peppers.
Cook until color changes.
Put into jars and put the hot vinegar mixture over them.
Seal.

title: cheese logs
directions: Soften cheeses at room temperature.
Mix cheese, garlic salt and chopped nuts.
Make into logs about the size of a round cracker.
Roll in a mixture of red pepper and paprika.
Wrap each roll in plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: e-z chicken and rice
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese; put back in oven for 10 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serves 4. Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Dumplings:
Make the day before.
Blend pie crust mix and flour with water with pastry blender.
Roll out very thin.
Cut in pieces, about 1-inch wide and 2-inches long.
Wrap in wax paper or Saran Wrap between layers.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Cut apples into chunks. Cut crescent rolls into smaller pieces. Wrap a piece of crescent roll around each chunk of apple. Heat water, sugar, butter and spices until boiling. Pour mixture over apples in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered until golden brown.

title: pelou
directions: Season chicken to
taste.
Cover
the
bottom of 4 quart pot with oil.
Let
oil
get
hot,
then
add
sugar until dark brown. Add chicken and stir with a little water.
Simmer until chicken is
cooked.
After
pouring
Pigeon
peas
(and coconut cream with water in can) are added.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Now add rice. Stir
until mixed.
Add water according to need. Turn flame down low and let cook.

title: banana pie(this pie is my daughter's favorite.)
directions: In a double boiler, place 2 3/4 cups of milk and cook until hot.
In a small bowl, mix flour, cornstarch (you can use 6 tablespoons flour if you have no cornstarch), the 1/4 cup milk, sugar, egg yolks and salt; beat well.
Add to hot milk and cook until thick.
Add vanilla, stir and let cool.
Pour half of custard into pie shell.
Slice 2 bananas and arrange in pie.
Add remaining custard.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add hash browns, mushroom soup, 1/2 pint sour cream, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Pour in a square dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Mix cornflakes with butter and sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Enjoy!

title: sally lunn(traditional bread)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine beaten egg yolks and milk.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until mixed; add shortening.
Fold in beaten egg whites (make sure they are stiff). Put in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon lush
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Form a crust and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Beat next three ingredients together.
Spread on first crust layer.
Beat next two ingredients together until thick.
Pour over second layer.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired. Refrigerate.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Beat pie filling, whipped topping mix, milk and vanilla on low speed until blended.
Beat until very thick (increase speed). Pour 1/3 in crust and layer with bananas.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: creole fried turkey injection recipe
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender or food processor.
Use injector to inject throughout thawed turkey. Deep-fry turkey 3 minutes per pound.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses.
Slowly beat in flour mixture alternately with hot water.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: cheesy tuna pot
directions: In a large pot, melt Velveeta and milk.
Add tuna and macaroni.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in butter until onions are translucent.
Add rest of ingredients and heat.
Add milk last and remove from heat when soup is hot.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and butter; add flour and mix well.
Add cereal and mix well with spoon.
Shape in small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add onion and other vegetables. Cook slightly.
Take from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into small balls and place in wonton wrappers.
Roll and seal ends.
