Deep fry in hot oil on medium heat, turning once, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: italian chocolate cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet an inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a lot, so you can cut it in half.

title: no wait rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cream margarine with sugar; add egg. Add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture, then stir in flour until well combined.
Drop spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tin and bake about 20 minutes at 350° until brown.
Store leftover dough in airtight bowl in refrigerator.

title: tuna stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in mushroom soup, sour cream, tuna and mushrooms.
Heat and serve on hot, cooked rice or noodles.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.) Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Combine the oil and egg in large mixing bowl.
Beat in the applesauce.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Add gradually to the batter, beating until smooth.
Stir in raisins and apple.
Bake in greased 9-inch round cake pan at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together, then add 3/4 box of vanilla pudding (small box).
Easy and good and pretty.

title: mexican chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl whisk together the oil, chili powder, oregano and cumin.
Crush tortilla chips to crumbs, pour in a shallow bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in seasoned oil, then roll in the ground chips until coated.
Set on foil-lined baking sheet and bake for 45 minutes, until browned and crisp outside, tender inside.
Serve hot.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep several days.

title: bean dip
directions: On bottom of large platter put refried beans.
Add avocados mashed with lemon juice.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Spread over bean and avocado mixture.
Add shredded cheese, tomatoes and sliced black olives.
Serve with your choice of chips.

title: "monkey bread"
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters with scissors.
Put 8 at a time in plastic bag with 3/4 of the sugar and cinnamon and shake.
Boil the 1 cup sugar and the margarine.
Pour over biscuits in well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn pan upside-down when you take it from oven.
Cool.
Break apart when cool.

title: ultra low-fat egg rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray large skillet with Pam buttery nonstick spray.
Brown cabbage, carrot, onion and seasonings for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add water and simmer and stir until tender.
Do not overcook.
Cool slightly.
Dip one side of egg roll wrapper in egg white.
This will be the outside.
Place about 1/3 to 1/2 cup of cabbage mixture just below center and roll up like an egg roll. Place on sprayed baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Entire recipe makes 6 servings. Grams of fat per serving, 1; calories per serving, 125.

title: apple dip
directions: Melt together oleo and brown sugar until brown sugar is dissolved.
While still hot add sour cream, vanilla and cinnamon to taste.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Cut up apples and dip into refrigerator mixture.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix nuts, cherries and crackers.
Melt margarine and marshmallows, then add milk over low heat.
Add melted mixture to cracker mixture and mix well.
Line loaf pan with waxed paper. Pour fruit cake into this and refrigerate.

title: turkey burger
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into patties.
Fry in butter on low heat.

title: cranberry stars
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Let set until gelatin is ready.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add syrup and chill until partially set.
Add cranberry mixture, pineapple, nuts and celery. Pour into mold(s).
Chill until firm.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Heat refried beans until soft. Spread on large round plate. After beans cool, spread with avocado dip, sour cream and sprinkle with chopped tomato and green onion. Top with grated cheese. Drizzle with taco or picante sauce.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Separate crescent roll dough into 8-inch triangles.
Place on a 12-inch pizza pan.
Press over bottom and up sides of pan.
Spoon sausage over crust; sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: salmon puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery

title: chicken tetrazzini(original recipe)
directions: Simmer chicken in water with 1 teaspoon salt about 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken; reserve broth.
Remove chicken from bones.
Return bones to broth; simmer 30 minutes.
Cool and skim off fat.
Cut chicken meat into strips or cubes.
You should have 2 cups.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, berries, oil, water and eggs.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: posol (mexican hominy dish)
directions: Sort, wash, soak and cook pinto beans about half-done.
Brown ribs (which have been washed and wiped dry) in large iron skillet or Dutch oven.
Remove ribs to pot with beans and saut onion and garlic in same pan.
Add to bean pot and simmer until ribs are very tender.
Add drained hominy and seasonings to taste and simmer about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mocha cooler
directions: Blend in a blender until smooth.

title: baked apples(8)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice bottoms off apples and core. Butter a large glass or porcelain dish and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Arrange apples upright in dish.
Fill the center of each apple with 1 teaspoon brown sugar, 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 piece of lemon peel.
Rub the top of each apple with 1/4 tablespoon soft butter and sprinkle with more sugar. Sprinkle the dried cherries around apples and add vanilla bean and cinnamon sticks to the dish.
Bake apples 30 to 45 minutes until soft.

title: cream sherbet punch
directions: In bowl combine pineapple juice, sherbet and ice cream.
Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into punch bowl. Gently stir in ginger ale.
Serve immediately.

title: lucky salad
directions: Bottom:
Melt
1 1/2 sticks butter or margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add
and mix 2 1/2 cups crushed pretzels.
Press in pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: heavenly crackers
directions: Melt butter and add sugar. Then boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour mixture over crackers that have been spread on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts. Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Take out of oven and remove crackers with spatula, placing on foil.
They break into sections after hardening.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
When they get tender, drain.
Pour 16 oz. sour cream into mixing bowl.
Add potatoes and Bacos.
Mix on medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Pour into greased 8 x 11 pyrex dish.
Grate cheese and spread on top.
Bake at 375 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: microwave broccoli and red peppers(lo-fat)
directions: Chop the broccoli into 3/4-inch pieces. Arrange in a 9-inch glass pie plate, with florets in the center and stems around the edges. Sprinkle with water. Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave on High 5 minutes or until tender. Drain and set aside.

title: yippy burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place the bottom of hamburger buns on cookie sheet.
Divide mixture evenly and spread on buns.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
When done, place tops on buns.
Place in container to steam buns.
Makes 12.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and beat well. Add other ingredients; mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes until lightly browned in 350° oven.
Make sure to flatten with a fork.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and pepper; drain well.
Add chili powder.
In a bowl, add egg, sour cream and tomato sauce.
Pour into meat mixture.
Spread five biscuits in bottom of large casserole dish.
Pour mixture on top of biscuits.
Spread the remaining five biscuits on top.
Sprinkle cheese on biscuits. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: greek salad
directions: Serve with Italian dressing, such as Good Seasons.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Soften cream cheese in microwave and then add to hot jello mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Add cold water, drained pineapple and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: strawberry cheesecake bars
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Combine eggs, corn syrup, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add chocolate.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until top puffs up.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Cook rice and broccoli separately. Mix all together.
Pour in casserole dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil well.
Add eggs; beat vigorously.
Add pumpkin and stir.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to first mixture, stirring well after each addition.
May add 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup white raisins, if desired.
Fresh pumpkin may be substituted for canned.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, eggs, milk and spice.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend margarine and cake mix in separate bowl, using cutter.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mix in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Spread 1/3 of crumbs in an 8 x 1/2-inch round pan.
Cover with half of oysters.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Using another 1/3 of the crumbs, spread a second layer; cover with remaining oysters. Sprinkle with pepper.
Combine cream, reserved oyster liquid, salt and Worcestershire.
Pour over oysters.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: carrot-bacon skillet
directions: Prepare and cook shredded carrots.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Drain fat, reserving two tablespoons.
Stir carrots, salt and pepper into fat in skillet. Heat through.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle bacon and parsley over carrots.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together 2 sticks margarine and 1/2 cup vegetable shortening.
Add, gradually, 3 cups granulated sugar.
Add 5 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1 cup milk, beating well after each addition.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Bake in a well-greased and floured large tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool in pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy in mixing bowl.
Add sugars, oil, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, soda, baking powder, zucchini and flour. Mix well.
Turn batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, pureed bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add salt, soda and flour.
Mix.
Pour into greased loaf pans (3 to 4) and bake at 300° for 1 hour. Freezes well.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Place rinsed potatoes in a large bowl.
Add egg, flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Heat oil over medium heat.
Drop batter by 1/3 cupful into hot oil; flatten to form pancakes.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: crackers
directions: Mix with more flour if necessary to make a stiff dough, as stiff as can be rolled out. (May be pounded and kneaded as many times as necessary.) Roll very thin and cut out round or square. Sprinkle lightly with salt and bake until lightly brown. Store in airtight container.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Make into ball, if desired. Chill.

title: nut roll
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add 3 beaten eggs.
Mix together. Add sifted flour and dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Chill overnight.
Separate into 4 parts.

title: peanut cake
directions: Combine milk and vinegar and let stand for 15 minutes.
Beat shortening until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Continue beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add soda to soured milk and stir. Then add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add the flour gradually, stirring after each addition, until well blended.
Add peanuts and lemon flavoring and stir.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut margarine into flour mixture until crumbly.
Add yeast/water and buttermilk to flour/butter until well blended.
Let stand for an hour or two covered with waxed paper.
Roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter or drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bone and cut fine. Mix all other ingredients with chicken.
Put into a large salad bowl.
Serves 12.

title: ranch beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put drained beans into baking dish.
Put water chestnuts and soup over beans.
Put crumbs and onion rings over mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake until mixture is bubbly.
One can of mushrooms may be added, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, carrots and oil.
Add nuts and raisins. Add eggs last.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: marci's fresh salsa
directions: Peel tomatoes and finely chop.
Finely dice onion, celery and green pepper.
Stir all ingredients together.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Place chicken breast halves on a preheated barbecue grill (or broiler pan) for 20 to 30 minutes or until cooked through. Meanwhile, in a medium sized bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, then brush over cooked chicken.
Grill for 5 more minutes.

title: spring garden salad
directions: Cook spirals 12 minutes and drain.
Mix the mayonnaise, water, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and turmeric together with whisk.
Add the onion, celery and carrots.
Add spirals to liquid mixture and marinate overnight.
Stir well before serving.
Makes 10 cups.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add pepperoni only to heat thoroughly.
Drain. Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour half the cooked pasta in baking dish. Spoon over half the sauce.
Next layer cottage cheese, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, remainder of pasta and remainder of sauce. Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: five layered casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Put sliced potatoes in bottom of dish, then drain corn and put on top of potatoes.
Layer carrots on top of corn.
Put browned hamburger and chopped onions on top of carrots.
Add pepperoni.
Add the can of tomato sauce.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; put shredded cheese on top. Heat until cheese is melted.

title: texas straw hats
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery just until clear and slightly crisp.
Combine hamburger and sauteed vegetables in large pot.
Add tomato paste, water, chili powder, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: In large bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set (3 hours).
Top with berries and glaze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon into a bowl.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs in a mixing bowl; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Spoon batter into a lightly greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 1 hour or until done.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and blend until smooth.
Slowly stir in broth, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Add half and half, slowly, and milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat over low flame.
Add milk if too thick.
Serve with sherry on the side to be poured over, if desired.

title: watermelon lemonade
directions: Fill each glass with ice and add one jigger each vodka and watermelon liqueur.
Fill with lemonade.
Garnish with lemon slices and fresh mint.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and cream and add milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Use ice cream freezer according to directions.

title: microwave mochi
directions: Microwave butter in microwave-safe dish for 45 seconds until melted.
In a mixing bowl, combine mochiko, 1 cup sugar and baking powder.
Gradually add milk, vanilla and melted butter while stirring.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave 9 to 12 minutes on High and rotate dish a quarter turn every 2 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Toss with kinako and sugar mixture until coated (optional).

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain juice from blueberries.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Boil.
Dissolve Jell-O; partially chill to set and fold in blueberries, pineapple and whipped cream. Return to chill in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip and walnut muffins
directions: In a large bowl, stir together sugars, flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, mix together milk, butter, eggs and vanilla until blended.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients. Add milk mixture and stir to combine. Stir in chips and nuts. Spoon batter into greased muffin cups (include greasing the edges around cups).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cake tester comes clean. Remove from oven and cool 5 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on rack. Serve warm or cold.

title: peach pie
directions: Place peaches in bowl. Toss with sugars and spices. Pour cream in and stir. Place mixture in pie shell. Place remaining pie shell on top and flute edges. Cut several slits in top to vent. Brush an egg white on the top and place in the oven at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and bake for an additional 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook cream, milk, sugar and butter over low heat until it makes a soft ball in cold water.
Break up the 1/4 pound of chocolate in a large bowl and add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring. Pour hot mixture over chocolate and beat until it is thick enough to spread over cake.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan, bottom and sides.
Layer in order as listed and on top sprinkle some more crushed Oreos.
Freeze and serve.

title: quick johnny cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Put into well-greased 10-inch iron skillet. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: dirt
directions: Mix pudding as directed in large bowl; add sugar and mix well. Whipped cream must be at room temperature; add to pudding.
Crush Oreo cookies to make bottom layer.*
Add mixture to cookies, then add remaining cookies to top.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cranberry butter
directions: In food processor, pulse berries, sugar and lemon rind.
Add cut up butter, a few pieces at a time.
Mold and refrigerate. Very tasty with poultry.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet; pour off grease.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until done.
Stir often.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix meal, flour and sugar.
Add enough hot water to mix.
Drop by tablespoon in skillet well-greased.
Cook until brown.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Beat well and add butter, milk and vanilla.
Cook in Pyrex dish until done.
Brown as you like.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil and 1/2 can crushed pineapple and all the juice; beat about 2 minutes and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: deep dish chicken pie
directions: Thaw pie crusts.
Mix soups, melted butter, vegetables, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook chicken breasts in salted water to which dehydrated onion has been added.
Cook, cut into chunks and add to other ingredients.
Pour into pierced bottom crust.
Place top crust and seal edges.
Bake at 350° until bubbling hot and crust is browned.

title: turkey stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing according to package directions.
Spoon stuffing into 1 1/2 quart shallow dish.
Form shell.
Combine soup, milk, peas, turkey and half of onions.
Pour into stuffing shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and top with rest of onions; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Shape meatballs.
Set aside.
Brown mushrooms and onions in 2 tablespoons oil; set aside.
Add remaining oil and brown meatballs, then remove.
Stir in flour and oil remaining in skillet.
Slowly stir in beef bouillon and heat until thick and smooth.
Add dry mustard and ketchup.
Add mushrooms and onions and meat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and serve over noodles.

title: stuffing
directions: Cut bread into cubes. Melt butter. Chop onions, and mix all ingredients. Stuff into bird or bake in greased cake pan till brown.

title: seven can chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except noodles or rice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Spoon apples into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine next 6 ingredients; stir until blended.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in 400° preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except Jiffy cornbread mix in large bowl. Let set overnight or for several hours.
Before cooking, stir in box of Jiffy cornbread mix.
Put all in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: vegetables in cheese sauce
directions: Place broccoli or cauliflower in shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inches).
Blend milk and soup.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in crusts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Best if baked in black skillet.

title: tex foley's cowboy soup
directions: In a large soup pot, brown the ground beef and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: italian rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, leaving cake in pan for 10 minutes.
Then remove from pan to cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve with rum flavored whipped cream.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening; add eggs and milk.
Beat until almost liquid.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix.
Add strawberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° until straw comes out clean. Start with 30 minutes.

title: lefse
directions: Cut shortening into potatoes.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Knead lightly.
Take some mixture and roll into a ball with hands.
Roll thin like pie crust on floured board or cloth.
Brown on medium ungreased grill pan until light brown and bubbly.
Then turn and repeat.
Place between 2 bath towels.

title: pretty punch
directions: Chill juices, mix together, stir in sugar. If mixing ingredients ahead of time, hold out ginger ale until ready to serve.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with sliced apples, pears, berries, etc.

title: old fashioned crackling bread
directions: Mix cracklings with dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and egg. Pour mixture into hot greased skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: chicken with garlic bread crumbs
directions: Mix bread crumbs, parsley, salt and garlic.
Dip chicken strips into egg.
Coat with bread crumb mixture. Melt butter in 10 inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken in butter 5-6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the center is no longer pink.

title: sweet potato, apricot casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, simmer apricots in water to cover (about 2 cups), 10 minutes or until soft.
Drain (reserving liquid).
Arrange sweet potatoes in a single layer in shallow dish; top with apricots and pecans.
Put reserved liquid and remaining ingredients in the saucepan, stir over moderate high heat until boiling; simmer 1 to 2 minutes, until thickened, pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake in a 375° oven 25 minutes, until sauce is bubbling and the pecans are browned.
Serves 10.

title: cauliflower-ham au gratin(8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange cauliflower in ungreased baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch), sprinkle with ham.
Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth; pour over ham.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake until topping is golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In bowl mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, crumbs, onion, Worcestershire, egg and pepper.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Spoon off fat; reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons drippings. In saucepan over low heat combine remaining soup, 1/4 cup water and reserved drippings.
Heat through; stir often.
Pour over sliced meat loaf.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: macaroni salad with kielbasa
directions: Cook macaroni but do not overcook.
Rinse immediately with cold water and drain a few minutes.
Turn into a large bowl. Slice and saute kielbasa; drain on paper towels.
Put 3-bean salad in freezer.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash sauerkraut and squeeze dry.
Add vinegar, water, oil, garlic salt and celery seed; mix.
Let stand several days.

title: shrimp boil
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Add ingredients and boil 1 minute, then add small potatoes and boil 15 minutes.
Add whole garlic cloves and onions.
Add corn-on-the-cob and boil until tender.
Add shrimp and boil until pink.
Drain and eat!

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans for 5 minutes (at a boil).
Then cover and let soak for an hour.
Drain water, add new.
Add sausage, cut into 1-inch pieces, onions, garlic, parsley, bay leaf, red (cayenne) pepper or Tabasco and lots of salt.
Cook on medium for about 2 to 3 hours until beans become soft and "gravy" becomes thicker. Serve over white rice.

title: red potato salad - heart healthy
directions: Broil potatoes on baking pan; spray with Pam and sprinkle with basil powder or Italian seasoning.
Turn after 2 to 3 minutes, until brown.
Combine other ingredients; stir well.
Add paprika and top with Parmesan cheese (nonfat).
Chill well and serve.

title: cornbread cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir with a spoon (do not overmix).
Pour into a greased and floured long cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole 3
directions: Melt margarine and add to dressing.
Layer in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish, dressing, chicken and soups.
Make 2 layers of each.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash and mash.
Add soup, sour cream, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Lightly grease casserole dish with margarine. Layer stuffing and squash mixture alternately with stuffing on bottom and top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic beefy v-8
directions: Place meat on large piece of foil and set in glass baking dish.
Sprinkle salt substitute and chili powder over meat; pour V-8 juice over meat.
Fold foil over meat and crimp edges to seal. Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes or until done to your taste. Yields 2 servings.
Exchanges:
4 lean meat; 1 vegetable; calories: 234; carb: 4 g; fat: 7 g: Pro: 36 g; Chol: 92 mg.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and pudding mix. Mix until smooth.
Add eggs.
Gradually add soda and flour.
Mix and add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and water and boil 5 minutes.
Add beets, sliced or diced, to hot mixture and allow to stand for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, bring to a boil and add butter.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy skillet, cook beef with salt until brown.
Stir to break into small pieces.
Transfer beef
to bowl and add remaining ingredients (save French fried onions
for topping).
Mix well; put into baking dish and bake 30
minutes, then
top
with onion rings.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: crawfish elegante
directions: In a saucepan, melt 1/2 stick butter and saute crawfish for 10 minutes.
Season with salt/red pepper.
While this is cooking, melt stick of butter in skillet and saute onions and parsley until wilted.
Add the flour and gradually add half and half.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Add salt and red pepper.
Boil 1/2 package egg noodles; drain.
Mix with other ingredients.

title: overnite vegetable salad
directions: Pour over drained vegetables.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serves 15.

title: hot subs
directions: Lay rolls open faced on cookie sheet.
Cut meat sliced in half.
Put one slice of each meat on rolls, dividing equally.
Top 1 side with onion slices, the other side with pepper rings and top one side with American cheese, the other with Swiss cheese.
Cut cheese so that it doesn't hang over sides of roll.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: autumn fruit salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and flour.
Stir in water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook and stir until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, combine apples, grapes and walnuts. Add the dressing; toss gently.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add sugar to eggs and mix well.
Add melted butter to eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Stir in raisins, nuts and rolled oats.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well; bake at 375° about 40 minutes or until firm.

title: patty shells
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Add water (enough to make a stiff dough).
On floured surface, roll 1/2 the dough out thin.
Cut circles out big enough to fit the bottom outside of a muffin tin.
Fit dough on carefully not to get holes.
Make 12 shells.
Put upside down on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until light brown.
Remove shells carefully and place right side up on cookie sheet and bake 5 more minutes.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream together the margarine and brown sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet; press flat with fork dipped in milk.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 8 minutes. Makes 50 truly delicious cookies.

title: dolores apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and vanilla along with the sifted flour, cinnamon, baking soda, oil, sliced, unpeeled apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chess pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown and set in the middle.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and oleo like dough and form into small balls.
Melt both chocolates and paraffin in double boiler. Dip balls by toothpicks in the chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix and roll thin.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla, salt and flour. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in egg whites.
Roll in nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Fill with your favorite filling (jams, jellies, decorator frostings, etc.).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook bacon.
Pour off all grease except 2 tablespoons.
Brown onions and garlic in this.
Add all ingredients. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mix well and bake until mixture bubbles.

title: apricot and pineapple salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from fruit.
Chill all. Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup of chilled juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Pour over large jar of spaghetti sauce.
Cook slow for 7 to 8 hours or on high for 6 hours.

title: sally's butter balls
directions: Thoroughly mix together the butter, vanilla and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Sift together and stir in the flour, salt and chopped nuts.
Chill dough at least for two hours.
After chilling, roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until very lightly browned on bottom. Roll in powdered sugar, or if you prefer, sprinkle on top only. Makes about 75 cookies.

title: reed surprise
directions: Season diced raw potatoes.
Fry in frying pan with butter until potatoes are tender.
Add bacon bits and any leftover vegetables you would like.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in desired dish to chill. Cut into squares and pass around.
This recipe is great for toddlers and preschool age children.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease pizza pan; slice cookies and arrange overlapped.
Press lightly together; flatten to make crust.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Edges will be lightly brown, but dough will not look done.
Cool completely.

title: yeast refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Beat 1 cup water, sugar and cooking oil into eggs.
Add yeast.
Stir in flour and salt, mixing well with spoon and then with hands.
Let rise.
You can keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 days in a covered bowl.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: You will need 1 large cookie sheet, 2 medium mixing bowls and 1 large casserole dish.

title: shrimp garden salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss with favorite salad dressing.
Serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Layer in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish with the following:

title: veal fricassee
directions: Cut meat in 2-inch cubes and parboil 20 minutes.
Drain off water and discard.
Add salt, pepper, spice and vegetables.
Add boiling water to cover and cook gently until tender, about 35 minutes.
Remove veal from pan and strain the stock.
Melt butter. Stir in flour and strained stock and cook to a smooth sauce (with veal added back in).

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° in 2 greased, floured glass loaf baking dishes.
Done when a toothpick comes out clean and dry.
May make 4 small loaves.
May put in a Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch cake pan also.

title: 1015 surprise casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in large skillet and saute onions until tender.
Place half the onions in 1 1/2-quart deep dish pie pan. Sprinkle 1 cup Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs over onions.
Repeat layers of onions and cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Add milk, eggs, vanilla and margarine; stir well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at slow temperature (325°) until golden brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crisp pear pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt. Slice oleo and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle 1/2 mixture in pie shell.
Spread sliced pears next.
Top with rest of sugar and flour mixture.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes.
Watch if browning too quickly; cover with foil.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pan (13 x 8 x 2-inch) and place in freezer.

title: mama's no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter, not margarine. Stir in sugar, salt, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes - no longer.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and cool.

title: slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, dry mustard and dill weed; bring to a boil.
Stir in oil.
Pour over cabbage, onion, carrot and green pepper.
Let set 24 hours.

title: grandma's brown bread(nut bread)
directions: In pan, combine water and raisins. Boil 2 minutes. Add margarine before removing from fire.
Make sure margarine is fully melted.
Let set 5 minutes, then add soda and stir well. Watch it, it foams.
In a bowl, combine beaten eggs, salt, vanilla and sugar. Add raisin mixture and mix well.
Add nuts, mix, then add flour.
Mix well.
Grease 6 (No.
303) cans.
Fill 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes, then run knife around and remove. Cool. Wrap in wax paper. Can be frozen.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream together the Crisco and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs (beaten), flour, baking powder, nuts and lemon rind.
Place in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When removed from the oven, poke holes in the top of the bread.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and the juice from a lemon together until dissolved.
Pour mixture into the holes that you make in the bread.
Cool and serve!

title: lemon cheesecake pie
directions: Mix for 2 minutes the milk and instant pudding.
Cream together the cream cheese and the thawed lemonade.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour into pudding and milk.
Pour into pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip.
This makes 2 pies.

title: vegetable sandwich(party sandwich)
directions: Mix
and let stand in refrigerator overnight; spread on round pieces of bread and garnish with a pimento.

title: grandma's gunger
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour a 15 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix molasses, oil, water, milk, eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Add raisins, if desired. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and let stand.
Beat eggs slightly. Beat in oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in alternately with apple sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased, floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream, whipped topping or Lemon Sauce.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Any other vegetables of your choice may be added or omitted.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken pieces well and pat dry.
Combine remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Add chicken pieces, pushing down into liquid to thoroughly moisten and coat.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.
Makes 6 servings, 120 calories per serving.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients using instructions on cake mix box.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured large Bundt pan. Add chocolate syrup to remaining batter and pour on top of first batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: crisp crusted chicken
directions: Beat egg and milk in bowl; set aside.
Mix potatoes, garlic and cheese.
Dip chicken in egg and milk, then in potato mixture. Place chicken in baking dish.
Top with melted margarine.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: layered salad
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in layers in large oblong dish. Spread mayonnaise over the top.
Sprinkle sugar, cheese, then bacon over the top.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: alabama "goober beans"
directions: Pick, sort and boil enough beans to fill crock-pot or use the cheapest (tasteless) canned beans and save an hour.
While beans are heating, dice salt pork into 1/2-inch cubes and rinse well in hot water.
Fry pork in skillet until foaming stops, then add to crock along with 4 tablespoons melted fat.
Add mustard, molasses, peanut butter and ginger.
May be eaten right away but flavor improves with long simmer in crock.
Adjust flavor to taste but use only enough peanut butter to thicken juice and not enough to recognize its flavor.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift meal, flour and salt together.
Add baking powder, eggs and onion.
Add milk, then drop from teaspoon into medium hot 275° fat; fry until golden brown.

title: grand marnier souffle
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Heat milk; add sugar.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Mix melted butter with flour and stir into boiling milk, blending until consistency is creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add Grand Marnier.
Beat egg yolks until lemon in color. Add to milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Gently fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and sugared souffle mould.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes with oven door closed the entire time. Serve immediately.

title: orange frosty
directions: Place orange juice, sugar and creamer in blender.
Blend at high speed about 1 minute; stop.
Add 6 to 8 ice cubes and blend until smooth and frosty.
Makes 2 large or 4 small servings.

title: sweet potatoes in orange cups
directions: Cut oranges in half crosswise.
Clip membranes and carefully remove pulp (do not puncture bottom).
Reserve orange pulp for other uses.

title: scallop chowder
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add scallops and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until scallops are cooked.
Remove and put aside.
Add onions, celery and carrots.
Cook for 7 minutes.
Add sage and white wine.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add milk.
Lower heat to simmer and clam juice.
Heat until hot.
Add potatoes and scallops.
Let simmer for 20 minutes, then serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put shortening and sugar in hot water; mix well and let cool in large bowl.
Mix beaten eggs and yeast in cold water in small bowl. Sift flour and salt.
Combine all ingredients and put in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Use what you want and roll and cut like biscuits.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise until double and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
These may be cut and placed on cookie sheet and frozen, then placed in plastic bags. Remove; place in greased pan 3 hours or thawed and doubled in size.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: To pork ribs, add water to 3/4 cover ribs.
Cover and cook until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and place in a shallow baking pan.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook bouillon, water, onions and celery for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and broccoli; cook for 30 more minutes, then add soup. Cut cheese into squares, then add.
Simmer until cheese is melted. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk bran muffins
directions: *Do not
use bran flakes or bran cereal.
Use raw bran, also referred to as miller's bran.

title: good dressing for fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple and lemon juices with sugar, flour and egg. Cook slowly until thick.
Let cool.
Drain well canned fruit. Slice bananas.
Mix fruits and dressing.
Cover with grated cheese.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Put in crust. Pour blueberries on top.
Chill.

title: texas cream cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except cinnamon and sugar, together at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour half into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle half sugar mix over batter.
Add rest of batter and sprinkle remaining sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper, onion and carrots.

title: gelatin salad with horseradish
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Allow to jell to egg white consistency.
Salt to taste.
Beat with electric beater until well blended.
Pour into mold and chill for 2 hours, until set.

title: sesame cookies
directions: To 1 dish of sesame seed, add 2 to 3 tablespoons water to moisten seeds so they will stick to the dough.

title: moma's miracle whip cake
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and water to the consistency of milk.
Sift together flour and cocoa.
Add to milk mixture along with all other ingredients.
Bake in two 8-inch cake pans at 375° for 30 minutes.
Good with powdered sugar icing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Heat butter and Coca-Cola until it boils.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture and mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, marshmallow and vanilla.
Beat well; pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat apricot brownie cake
directions: Simmer water and apricots in small covered saucepan for 20 minutes.
Pour into blender or food processor and puree until smooth.
Scrape into a medium size bowl.

title: beef roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place in pan with small amount of oil.
Top with onions.
Roast, uncovered, for 2 hours at 325° until lightly brown.
Add hot water.
Mix flour with small amount of hot water to make a paste.
Pour around roast.
Add more salt, pepper and Accent.
Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Pour 1 c. boiling water over frozen broccoli.
Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Mix the broccoli and water with the soup.
Slightly melt the cheez whiz (I do this in the microwave.) and add to broccoli and soup mixture.
Add the sauteed vegetables.
Add the uncooked rice, mix altogether and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Do not cover.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes, (until
bubbly) at 350.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: garden fresh macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni by directions on box; rinse and drain.
Add vegetables, cheese and pickles to macaroni.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and salt.
Mix with the macaroni mixture.
Chill.

title: choco chip cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine softened butter, salt and confectioners sugar; beat with an electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add flour little by little to the butter mixture, beating with a wooden spoon.
Add chocolate chips and crushed corn flakes.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoons on baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes. Take out from oven and flatten the cookies using the back of a spoon and put back in the oven for 10 minutes.
Take out and cool on a cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 large cookies, 3 inches in diameter.

title: chinese rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Cook steak until tender.
Add olives, pickles, onions, beef cubes, onion salt and garlic salt.
Sprinkle gravy mix over this and simmer a few minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan or glass long dish, place a layer of wafers and bananas. Mix milk and pudding until smooth.
Add sour cream and
Cool Whip. Mix and pour 1/2 of pudding over wafers. Add bananas, then add another layer of wafers, bananas and finish with remaining pudding.

title: mozzarella marinara
directions: Fold string cheese in egg roll wrapper.
Tuck ends in toward seam.
Put oil in a large frying pan.
Put wrappers, seam side down in oil and put on medium heat.
Brown wrappers on all sides. Remove from fry pan and use paper towels to absorb excess oil. Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes. Serve with warmed pizza sauce.
Makes 18.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix corn muffin mix, egg and milk until just moist. Set aside. Mix ground beef and sausage, onion and garlic in square 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Microwave at High until meat loses pink color, 5 to 9 minutes, stirring once to break up meat.
Drain.

title: carrot-zucchini bar cookies with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking pan.
Beat together brown sugar, butter and cream cheese in large bowl with electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.
Stir in carrots, zucchini and raisins.
Spoon into prepared pan evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Invert cake on wire rack; cool completely.
Spread frosting on top.

title: beef liver and onions
directions: Dredge liver with mixed flour, salt and pepper.
Heat 1/4 cup bacon drippings; brown liver in it quickly on both sides.
Remove to hot platter and keep warm.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix boiling water and lime Jell-O. Mix well. Add sugar, then add rest of the ingredients. This mixture makes 5 quarts. Freeze this mixture, then 2 1/2 hours before serving time, remove from freezer. Add 2 quarts ginger ale, Sprite or Atreat-Treatum. Mixture should be slushy. Very refreshing drink.

title: mary's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls (approximately 16 to 20).
Bake in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn the meatballs after the first 10 minutes of baking.

title: stuff
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook egg noodles according to package.
Layer ingredients in a casserole pan.
Cook, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in large casserole dish. Melt 1 stick butter in pan.
Add 2 cups Ritz crackers to butter. Put on top of casserole.
Let stand refrigerated overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves at least 12 people.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in water; pour on cukes and onions.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Mix vinegar, mustard seed, sugar and water and bring to a boiling point.
Add turmeric.
Pour into hot clean jars. Let stand for a couple of weeks before eating.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: For marinade, combine 2 tsp. soy sauce, 2 tsp. sherry, 2 tsp. cornstarch and salt in large bowl; mix well.
Add chicken; stir to coat well.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 3 tsp. soy sauce, 3 tsp. sherry, chicken broth, vinegar, sugar and remaining 1 1/2 tsp. cornstarch in small bowl; mix well and set aside.
Heat 1 tbsp. oil in wok or large skillet over medium heat.
Add peanuts and cook until golden.
Remove peanuts and set aside.
Heat remaining 2 tbsp. oil in wok over medium heat.
Add chili peppers and stir-fry until peppers just begin to darken, about 1 minute. Increase heat to high.
Add chicken and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add ginger; stir-fry until chicken is cooked through, about 1 minute more.
Add onions and peanuts to wok.
Stir cornstarch mixture and add to pan; cook and stir until sauce boils and thickens.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix ingredients together until crumbly.
Spread over apples. Drizzle with 1/3 cup oil.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy.
Mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Roll balls into sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a chocolate kiss; press down firmly so cookie cracks around the edge.
Let cool.
Ready to eat!

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Scrub and slice cucumbers into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric spice, celery seed, prepared mustard and mustard seed and bring to a boil.
Pour in cucumbers, green peppers and onions and bring back to a boil.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes over medium heat.
Sterilize jars.
Add a pinch of alum to each jar and fill with pickle mixture and seal.

title: aunt pearl's favorite sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg and 1 egg yolk; beat well.
Add lemon rind.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, working in flour with hands as dough stiffens.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill thoroughly. Roll out part of dough at a time to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
(Refrigerate remainder.) Cut in desired shapes with small cookie cutters.
Dilute remaining egg white with a very small amount of water.
Brush on cookies.
Decorate as desired.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: crab rangoons
directions: Preheat oil in your wok.
If you are using an electric wok, set the temperature to 400°.
In a bowl, mix the cream cheese and the crab thoroughly.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Place about a teaspoon of the mixture onto the center of the wonton wrapper. Dip finger in water and wet the edges of the wrapper.
Fold wrapper to form a triangle.
Drop several into oil, turning until all sides are browned, about 30 seconds per side.
Remove and drain excess oil.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients to water.
Mix in.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add to macaroni.
Add soup and meat and mix well. Place in greased casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: seafood croissant
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Add shrimp, mayo, salt, pepper and garlic powder to broccoli.
Spoon filling into pastry dough.
Roll into crescent.
Brush with melted butter. Bake per crescent roll directions.

title: light banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package. Stir in Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip; mix well on low speed. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture in large bowl. Refrigerate.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together the soup, margarine and cream cheese; melt on stove.
Slice potatoes and put 1/2 into 2-quart baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of melted mixture on top.
Cover with Velveeta cheese.
Add rest of potatoes.
Pour rest of mixture on top.
Cover with another layer of Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: festive fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 12-cup fluted tube or 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients except corn syrup; stir by hand until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 30 minutes; loosen edges and remove from pan. Cool completely.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil and store in refrigerator.
Glaze with warm corn syrup before serving. Decorate with additional candied fruit and nuts, if desired. Yield:
24 to 36 servings.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt, cornstarch and egg yolks; cook until thick.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and butter.
Put into a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and pumpkin thoroughly in a large bowl.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Blend well.
Add raisins and pecans.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: low-fat rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until milk is hot but not boiling!!!
Pour into a baking dish sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8!!

title: garlic broccoli
directions: Cook garlic in oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add broccoli and next four ingredients; cover and cook 5 minutes or until crisp to tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Put 1/3 cup margarine in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt in oven.
Remove pan from oven and layer the bottom with ingredients in order.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Loosen edges; cool in pan.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients together. Cook in 9 X 13 pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Chill all ingredients thoroughly before use and flour.	Cut in shortening; mix well.
Dissolve salt in ice water; add to flour mixture.
Mix long enough to wet flour; do not overmix.
Roll out the pie dough as few strokes as possible.
The top piece should be slightly thinner than the bottom.
Bake at 400° to 450° until golden brown.
Yields 2 (8-inch) pie crusts.

title: holiday gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in hot applesauce.
Cool.
Add celery and 1 cup 7-Up.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Mix pudding with milk according to the directions.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers. Cover with half of pudding mixture.
Make another layer of crackers, followed by the rest of pudding.
Make final layer of crackers and spread with frosting.
Chill.

title: potato pudding (kugel)(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Peel potatoes; grate, using coarse grater.
Turn into colander; place in a large bowl so excess liquid will drain off. There should be 6 cups drained potatoes.

title: russian tea cake
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and vanilla good. Sift flour and salt together.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased baking sheets at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes; not too brown. While still warm, roll in powdered sugar. When cool, roll again in powdered sugar.

title: slim jim chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in Dutch oven or large frypan. Thoroughly drain all excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve hot. Makes 8 (1 cup) servings at 156 calories a serving.
This dish freezes well.

title: diet toast spread
directions: Combine fruit and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Continue to boil for 3 minutes.
Add artificial sweetener and gelatin. Stir and cook for an additional minute.
Remove from heat and cool before storing.
Refrigerate as soon as cooled.

title: fried rice - local style
directions: Fry meats in
wok;
drain
excess
oil.
Add onions and string beans.
When
vegetables
are
cooked,
pour
in oyster sauce and shoyu.
Amount of liquids is based on amount of rice used.	For this
recipe,
I suggest 3 cups of cooked rice.
(I use freshly cooked
rice,
not	old
rice.) Add rice; mix with shakushi (Japanese
rice
paddle).
If
not	enough sauce, add more shoyu and
oyster sauce.	Season according to your taste. Mix in fried eggs.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix blueberries with 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bring to boil and save juice.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups water.
Add 1/2 cup blueberry juice and 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Let get very firm.

title: italian cookie(dunk)
directions: Mix oil and sugar and beat well.
Add milk, eggs, baking powder and flavors.
Beat well and add flour (whatever it takes). Let it stand for about ten minutes.
Roll dough like bread sticks and tie into knots, two inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or light brown.
Cool and glaze.

title: southern delight
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; place in Pyrex dish. Parboil the chicken and place on top of mixture.
Prepare the stuffing as directed and put on top of chicken in Pyrex dish. Bake, covered, at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: roast opossum with vegetables
directions: Salt and pepper the opossum.
Saute chopped onion in vegetable oil.
Add bread cubes, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and some sage to taste.
Add some water and mix thoroughly.
Stuff the opossum cavity with this stuffing and sew up.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan and place bacon strips across the back.
Roast, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place vegetables around the opossum, salt and pepper to taste and roast an additional hour or until the meat and carrots are tender.

title: pop cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan according to instructions.
After cake has been removed from oven, poke holes all over cake. Mix jello, 1 1/2 cups boiling water and pop in bowl; pour over cake. Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip in a bowl.
After cake is cool, frost with Cool Whip mixture. Store in refrigerator.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes; cool.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut deer meat into 1/4-inch strips or smaller.
Put the strips in a large pan or use a 1 gallon Ziploc baggie.
The baggie is less messy.
Pour the Allegro marinade over the strips and let it set overnight in the refrigerator.
Place all the deer strips in the dehydrator (don't overlap the strips).
Next you sprinkle on your seasonings according to your own taste.
Turn the dehydrator setting to 140° and let it cook for 12 hours.
It's good to experiment with different types of seasoning until you hit on the right one for you.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Cook beef (can be made with game meat too) in a large pan. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add bouillon and all other ingredients to pan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for at least 1/2 hour, the longer the better.
Cook 2 pounds spaghetti noodles. Serve chili on top of noodles, topping with some sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until it falls apart.
Drain.
Add cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup.
Sprinkle shredded cheese and bread crumbs over the top.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix this together and press into bottom of grease pan.

title: grandma's never fail rosettes
directions: In a deep saucepan, heat 2 to 3-inches of oil to 400°.
In a bowl, slightly beat eggs with sugar and salt.

Add milk, flour, cornstarch and vanilla. Heat rosette iron by placing in the hot oil for 1 minute. Tap off excess oil from iron onto paper towels. Dip hot iron into batter just to top of edge (don't go over top). Dip into oil and fry until golden brown (about 30 seconds). Immediately invert rosette on paper towel to cool. Heat iron in hot oil again and tap on paper towel before making another rosette.
Just before serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and remove bones from salmon.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add grated cheese, egg, salt, pepper and flour; mix well. Place in baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and onion.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil (375°), frying only a few at a time, until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: just crispy candy
directions: Melt almond bark (try melting in microwave), then mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, cocoa and milk hard for 1 minute.
Take from fire and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, Crisco, sugar and brown sugar.
Add in this order:
eggs, salt, baking soda, vanilla, flour, oats and chocolate chips.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until golden but not brown on edges of pan.
This originally was a recipe for cookies.
The temperature stays the same but shorten cooking time when making cookies.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients together in order.
Bake in 3 round pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour; mix well. Shape in balls.
Dip in 2 slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down center of cookie with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Fill center with jelly.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Store dry mixture in a covered container. To serve, use 2 teaspoons per cup of water (hot or cold).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins or line with paper baking cups.
Combine all ingredients except blueberries.
Add blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: sherbet party punch
directions: Combine orange juice, grapefruit juice, lemonade and cold water.
Stir until melted.
Add 1 tray ice cubes and 1/2 sherbet. Let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining sherbet and ginger ale. Yield:
25 servings.

title: potato cheese scallop
directions: Arrange potatoes in buttered dish.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut up carrots in bite size pieces.
Add some brown sugar and butter in saucepan and heat up.
Cook carrots until done.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, combine butter, sugar and pumpkin; mix well. In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, oatmeal and pecans; stir to blend. Add to pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly. Spread evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake for 16 to 18 minutes. Immediately upon removing from oven, pour glaze over bars. Let cool and cut.

title: layered salad
directions: Cut lettuce into small pieces and put into large storage type bowl.
Cut cauliflower into small flowers and layer on top of lettuce.
Add chopped onion for next layer.
Spread Miracle Whip evenly and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with bacon and sugar. Refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: fruity bundt cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla. Combine 2 cups flour and baking powder. Gradually beat into batter. Combine pecans, cherries and remaining flour. Fold into batter. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done. Cool in the pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: barbecue deer hind quarter and sauce
directions: Put hind quarter in foil. Sprinkle with spices; pour Italian dressing over it. Cover with foil. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Open foil and put on smoker using oak or Mesquite wood. (To expedite cooking time, place in 300° to 350° oven covered for 2 to 3 hours.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, salt, oil, vanilla and eggs. Then stir in zucchini. Pour into two greased bread pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool on rack.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in well-buttered 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
Pour evenly over the bread and cheese.
Sprinkle cooked sausage and optional ingredients over the top.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat with seasonings and let simmer 30 or 45 minutes.
Take corn tortillas and soften in hot grease just a second.
Drain and roll with meat mixture, cheese and onion.
Top with small can of chili and enchilada sauce mixture.
Cover with onion and cheese and bake until hot.

title: cherry spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add alternately the flour and milk in which soda is dissolved. Add unbeaten egg whites one at a time, beating the mixture well. Then add apples, nuts, cherries and spices. Cook at 275° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: pretty salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cook and drain ground beef with onions and bell pepper.
Add the ingredients together and add half the cheese.
Put in baking dish; top with remaining cheese.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together in mixing bowl, powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add pudding mix, Cool Whip and milk.
Crush cookies in 8 or 8 1/2-inch flower pot.
Layer mixture, cookies, mixture, cookies, etc., ending with cookies on top.
Add flower, plant, gummy worms, etc.
Serve with spade, line pot with colored Saran Wrap.

title: pedro's special
directions: Grease casserole.
Brown meat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until the onion is transparent.
Add tomato sauce and paste, oregano and chili powder.
Place layers of meat sauce alternately with layers of beans and corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes more.

title: jo-jo potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes.
Dredge slices in mix or put in plastic bag and shake.
Place in Pyrex dish.
Cut up 1 stick margarine over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak 2 brans together. Mix and let cool. Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well. Sift together flour, salt and soda. Alternate other ingredients (bran, oil, flour and buttermilk). Mix well. Spoon into paper muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or more.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Put all ingredients in 8-inch round dish and cover with plastic.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 minutes more.
Combine 1/2 cup shredded cheese, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and 1/4 teaspoon paprika.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes. Cook, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: jello ice cream dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool.
When partly congealed, add drained, crushed pineapple. Whip and then fold in the ice cream.
Put into the refrigerator until set. Serves 10 to 12.

title: delicious meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; shape into balls.
Mix next 4 ingredients together in a pressure pan.
Heat.
Drop in meatballs and cook 15 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.
Pour cold water over pan to cool rapidly.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding
mix,
butter, milk, eggs and oil in a large bowl.
Prepare cake as directed on package.
Mix in coconut and pecans.
Put
in
tube	pan,
greased
and floured lightly. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.	Cool on rack for 1 hour. Remove cake from
pan
and let stand overnight before serving.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, in oven.
Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Place chicken, skin sides down, in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake about 30 minutes longer or until juice is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut.

title: wassail
directions: Heat all ingredients together until sugar is dissolved.
Serve warm with cinnamon stick.

title: lemon dessert roll
directions: Beat until thick and lemon colored at high speed the eggs. Gradually beat in at medium speed the sugar.
Beat in all at once at same speed the water and vanilla.
Sift together and beat into egg mixture all at once at low speed the sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth and well blended.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Prepare the meatballs in a size of your choice; place into a baking dish.
Place in the oven; bake at 400° until they are about half done.
Take them out; drain off the grease.
To make the sauce, dissolve the cranberry sauce and the Heinz cocktail sauce in a saucepan at low heat.
Mix well; pour over the meatballs. Cover; place them back in the oven.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. (Makes a very good appetizer.)

title: 1 2 3 pound cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk and set aside while you mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together.
Stir in all ingredients.
Pour into a large greased and floured tube pan.
Put cake into a cold oven. Turn oven on at 325° and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before turning out onto plate.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve hot.
(Note:
Best if made a day ahead.)

title: crisp noodle chicken
directions: Bring roast to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook roast at 500°
for 5 minutes per pound plus 10 minutes (e.g. a 3 pound roast would cook for 25 minutes).

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(May use 8 ounce can of refried beans.)

title: gran's fish chowder
directions: In a large 6-quart pot, place fish and cover with water.
Boil until flaky.
Remove from fire and bone fish. Return boneless meat, potatoes, onion and margarine to pot and cook well done. Add canned milk and fresh milk to fill pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat until very hot, but do not boil.
Serve with saltine crackers or soup crackers.
For thicker soup, mix 2/3 cup cornstarch with water and add to fish-vegetable mixture. Cook until thick, then add milk.

title: mountain momma mudslide cake
directions: First Layer:
Blend oleo, flour and pecans with pastry blender.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex or aluminum pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mom's chili soup
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
While meat is browning, mix all other ingredients together in slow cooker and start heat.
Drain grease from meat and add to slow cooker.
Simmer 3 hours at low heat, stirring now and then.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add raisins, nuts and coconut, then add vinegar.
Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with fresh whipped cream.

title: low-fat strawberry yogurt pie
directions: In blender, puree enough strawberries to equal 3/4 cup. Reserve remaining berries for garnish.
In medium saucepan, mix unflavored gelatin with 1/4 cup sugar.
Blend in egg yolks, beaten with milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved (about 5 minutes).
With wire whisk or rotary beater, blend in pureed strawberries, yogurt, lemon juice and food coloring.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tennessee biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.

Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add buttermilk and water to dry ingredients. Mix and roll into a ball. Cover tightly and place in refrigerator. When ready to bake, dip in melted butter and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: frosted cinnamon raisin bars
directions: Combine sugars, margarine and flour.
Mix until crumbly.
Press 2 cups of this mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients to crumb mixture and mix well.
Pour evenly over crust. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes; drizzle with frosting and sprinkle with nuts.

title: savory crust chicken and turkey pie
directions: Combine butter (softened), sour cream and egg; beat until smooth.
Lightly grease baking dish.
Spoon mixture into the dish. Spread and pat down crust all over the bottom and up the sides of the baking pan.

title: waikiki chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Meanwhile, combine undrained pineapple, barbecue sauce, cornstarch, brown sugar and mustard. Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender, about 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: smokey brisket
directions: Combine seasonings and pour over brisket; marinate overnight. Place brisket in a roaster (on rack) and cover with foil, then place lid on roaster.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
Add beans and heat in microwave until hot.
Spread tortilla chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Put bean-meat mixture on top of chips.
Top with shredded cheese and heat until the cheese is melted.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Add oleo and mushrooms to pan.
Saute.
Put patties back in with mushrooms.
Mix brown gravy mix with water and wine.
Add to patties, cover and simmer.
Stir gently occasionally.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Fill a deep pie tin with peeled and sliced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 2 tablespoons of sugar to taste.
Add bits of butter and a few drops of water.
Put in oven while making batter. Combine the rest of the ingredients with hand beater.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
When done, loosen edges and invert on large platter.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: straw and hay fettuccine
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add cream and stir in Parmesan cheese.
Just heat (do not allow mixture to come to boil).
Pour over hot drained pasta.
Season with fresh pepper. Serve with additional Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: candied yams
directions: Slice yams and sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon, cloves, butter and salt.
Place in a baking dish that contains the water and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until yams are tender.

title: lemony glaze
directions: Combine lemonade mix, water and melted butter.
Add sifted powdered sugar and blend well.
Spoon over lemonade cake.

title: caramel peanuts
directions: Boil together until liquid is mostly absorbed and nuts are tacky.
Stir occasionally.
Spread out in jelly roll pan and sprinkle with salt.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Blend with mixer cheeses, salts and sauces.
Return to refrigerator and chill.
Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.
May use English walnuts or salted peanuts.
Chill and serve with favorite snack crackers.

title: dump-it dessert cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan, spread pineapple.
Top with pie filling; sprinkle dry cake mix over this.
Slice oleo into 12 slices and put over top.
Cover all with coconut.
Bake 1 hour until golden.
Serve with ice cream or whip cream if desired.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix first four ingredients like pie crust; let chill 2 hours or until dough is easy to handle.
Make into balls, put on wax paper lined cookie sheet and chill all night.
Melt chocolate chips with vegetable oil.
Dip balls into melted chocolate and roll in crushed nuts.
Let cool.
