title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter in saucepan on low heat. Stir well and remove from heat; add sugar and mix well.

Roll into small balls. Refrigerate on wax paper for at least 30 minutes. Melt wax and chips in top of double boiler. Dip cooled balls into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper. Toothpicks make dipping easier.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, garlic, tomato sauce, rice and seasonings.
Fill zucchini boat with ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese and then corn chips.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chip beef on toast
directions: Melt butter in a pan, add flour to thicken.
Add milk stirring over medium heat.
Cut up chip beef and add to mixture. Cook over medium heat until sauce thickens and meat is tender. Pour over two slices of toasted bread.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make a day before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop vegetables and peppers in food processor.
Mix all ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator.
One can of tuna can be added if you like.

title: beaufort stew
directions: In a large pot, add crab and fill half full of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add ingredients in this order:
onion, bell pepper, sausage, potatoes, corn, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
May need to add more water before cooking if items aren't submerged.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
Mix wet ingredients together and then add to dry.
Bake in one large loaf pan, well-greased at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Place Crisco, sugar and salt in dish and pour warm milk over; mix.
Add beaten egg and yeast to this mixture; then add enough flour to make a cake batter dough. Let rise about double; then roll in more flour and make rolls and let rise again (about 2 hours).
Bake at 350° to 375°.
Place surplus dough in refrigerator.

title: meatballs with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine thoroughly beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Shape into 35 meatballs.
Chill 1 hour.
Melt butter in electric skillet.
Brown meatballs.
Spoon out extra grease.
Combine soup and water.
Add to meatballs and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: choc-oat chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar with nuts and set aside.
Mix everything together, except apples.
When the ingredients are well mixed, add chopped apples.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle sugar and nut mixture over cake batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry pies
directions: Cook pie shells.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and pecans together.
Blend until smooth.
Divide mixture into 2 cool, baked pie shells.
Next, divide blueberry pie filling into shells. On top, place Cool Whip, leaving only the center of the pie showing the blueberry mixture.

title: new potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When cool, grate potatoes.
Mix potatoes, sour cream, milk, salt, 1/2 cup each cheese and onions. Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: quick cobbler pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour into baking dish over melted butter.
Add fruit on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Salt and pepper venison cubes.
Brown lightly in 2 tablespoons butter or oil.
Remember to remove as much fat as possible from the meat.
Place celery and onions in a crock-pot.
Add browned meat and other ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 12 hours or on high for 4 to 6 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice or buttered noodles.

title: chili(low-fat)
directions: Cut bottom round into long, thin slices, then cut across.
Put into bowl and add 1 tablespoon olive oil; mix.
Pour into hot pan and stir-fry in small amounts.
Stir-fry ground round.
Put stir-fried meat into large Dutch oven.
Add cumin, tomato paste, onion, garlic and jalapeno.
Add 1 cup wine and 1 cup water. Simmer for 1 hour, then add 1 cup wine and 1 cup water; simmer again.

title: fried apple slices
directions: Core apples, leaving skin on.
Cut into rings.
In large skillet, melt the butter.
Add the apple slices and cook for about 3 minutes per side or until slightly browned.
(Cook in batches.) Combine the sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over cooked apples. Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Measure all dry ingredients and mix.
Add oil and eggs and beat together with dry ingredients.
Add carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: fisherman casserole
directions: In skillet melt butter; cook celery, green pepper and onion. Blend in flour until smooth; gradually add milk, stirring until thick.
Add Blue cheese dressing, pimentos, salt and pepper.
Add fish and shrimp.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake 15 minutes. Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake 10 minutes more or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: tiger stripes
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter over very low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Pour into wax paper lined pan.
(Jelly roll pan for thinner candy or a 9 x 9-inch pan for a thicker candy.)
Pour melted chocolate chips over the first layer.
Cut through with a knife to marble.
Chill.
Cut into small bars.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut meat into long strips.
Place all ingredients in a tightly covered container.
Marinate overnight.
Hang on top rack of oven rack with toothpicks.
Bake at 200° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Line bottom of oven with foil for easy cleanup.

title: mallow clusters
directions: Heat corn syrup to boiling in 3 quart saucepan.
Reduce heat. Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
Fold in cereal until well coated.
Fold in marshmallows.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let clusters stand at room temperature until firm, about 2 hours.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions on box.	Let cool. Mix mayo or salad dressing with sugar.
Add onions, green pepper, celery or other vegetables.
Mix well.
Add chopped tomatoes.
Mix gently.
Crumble 1/2 of cornbread in 2-quart casserole.
Add bacon or bacon bits.
Add vegetable mixture on top of this.
Top with other 1/2 of crumbled cornbread.
Can add paprika or bacon bits on top for color.
Refrigerate.
Can be made night before.

title: layered golden salad
directions: Add shredded cheese before mayonnaise mixture.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar, then pour over mixture before you serve it.
Add bacon bits on top of mayonnaise mixture.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Stir until drink mix dissolves.
Divide mixture evenly into 4 gallon size, heavy-duty zip-top plastic bags; freeze.
Remove each bag 1 hour before serving.
Place in punch bowl and break into chunks.
Add 2 bottles ginger ale into each bag of mixture.
Stir until slushy. Yield:
2 1/2 gallons or 2 1/2 quarts per bag of mixture.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil sealed cans of milk three hours with water covering cans throughout boiling.
Let cool 10 minutes, then pour in pie crust. When completely cool, top with Cool Whip, nuts, chocolate chips, and cherries.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into a 1-quart casserole.
Add onion and pepper.
Cover; cook in microwave 4 1/2 to 7 1/2 minutes, or until sausage is set and vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; microwave 6 1/2 to 9 minutes, or until heated through, stirring once.

title: easy quiche
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and margarine.
Mix eggs, milk, soup and flour.
Add butter, onions and peppers.
Place cooked broccoli and cheese in pie crusts.
Pour mixture over them. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all; toss to mix.

title: congealed broccoli salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup consomme.
Cook and drain broccoli, then chop fine.
Heat consomme; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Then add other ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan or a mold.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Serves 10.

title: kraut
directions: Mix well.
Pack kraut in jars.
Put mixture over the kraut and seal.

title: kathy's special pasta
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, grated cheese, dash of pepper, Ricotta and Polly O cheese (grated) until well blended.
Boil pasta for about 15 minutes or to taste (soft or al dente).
Strain pasta and pour into baking pan with stick of butter.
Blend well. Then add your other ingredients.
Mix well and spread all over pasta.

title: dip for fresh fruits
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together.
Add pineapple juice to consistency needed.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini or summer squash casserole
directions: Cut unpeeled squash into bite size pieces.
Lightly cook and drain.
Mix dressing with butter.
Mix all ingredients with 1/2 of dressing mixture.
Put in casserole and top with the balance of the dressing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat slowly.
Serve with Escort crackers.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Mix as you go along.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: garlic spaghetti
directions: Melt butter.
Use garlic press and brown in butter.
Add milk and melt cheese on low heat.
Place all ingredients in casserole. When ready to serve, put casserole in a 250° oven until spaghetti is hot.
Best prepared early and allowed to sit until ready to heat and serve.

title: bread-raisin pudding
directions: Place bread cubes in greased crock-pot.
In a bowl mix eggs, well-beaten, sugar, melted butter and milk.
Stir until smooth. Add raisins and nutmeg.
Pour over bread.
Mix lightly and cook on high 1 hour, then low 3 to 4 hours.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: hot-water cornmeal cakes
directions: Toss together the first 5 ingredients.
Meanwhile, heat the oil at medium high in a deep medium sized skillet until it begins to smoke slightly.
Stir the boiling water into the cornmeal mixture.
(Add more cornmeal as needed.
You should end up with a stiff paste you can push off the end of a spoon.)
Form rounded tablespoonfuls of the mush, flatten slightly and drop into the hot oil.
Fry until crisp and golden, about 4 minutes.
Remove the cakes with a slotted spoon to drain on paper towels.
Keep warm. Makes about 30 pieces.

title: hamburger stew and dumplings
directions: Make ground beef into small balls.
Roll them in flour, add salt and pepper and brown them.
Prepare onion soup according to directions, plus 1 cup water.
Add this to hamburger.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook until carrots and potatoes are almost done.
Prepare a batter of Bisquick dumplings.
Drop them in stew and cook, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: danish goulash
directions: Cut beef into 1/4-inch cubes; brown in hot oil with a speck of pepper.
Add onions, and stir until lightly browned.
Add salt, 2 1/2 cups cold water, sugar and bay leaves.
Cover; simmer 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Remove bay leaves, then stir in flour and 5 teaspoons water, blended together.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Serve over mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over broccoli.
Marinate overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Cover potatoes with water and boil until barely tender. Saut onion in margarine. Add mixture to potatoes. Add soup and dip; heat thoroughly. Add milk and heat slowly. Do not boil. When served, top with grated cheese, crumbled bacon and chopped green onions.

title: doggie treats
directions: Boil water.
Dissolve bouillon cubes.
Add shortening.
Mix flour and oatmeal, stir in liquid mix. Form into dough and roll out on floured surface.
Cut into 1/4 inch shapes. Bake in preheated 300° oven for 30 minutes, or until brown.
Best if left to cool and harden overnight.
Yields approximately 36 doggie biscuits. or the other.

title: strawberry-banana  salad
directions: Add jello to 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Put half of mixture in bottom of pan.
Chill until firm.
Top with sour cream. Add remaining mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: party line cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients after sifted together.
Cut Snicker bars into halves.
Wrap a piece of dough around each piece of Snicker.
Bake at 350° about 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not bake until edges are brown.
Makes about 58.

title: spinach cheese strata
directions: Cut bread in thin slices; line bottom of buttered 6 cup baking dish with 1/2 the slices.
Saute onion in butter 5 minutes. Squeeze spinach dry and add to pan with dill, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Stir.
Spread spinach over bread; sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Arrange remaining bread, overlapping on top.
Beat eggs; stir in milk and remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour over bread. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until puffed and golden.
If browns fast, cover with foil.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: anadama bread
directions: In large bowl, combine yeast and 3 cups flour.
Gradually stir cornmeal into boiling water.
Add molasses, shortening and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add to flour/yeast mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: butter rum shrimp
directions: In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of margarine; add salt, pepper and shrimp.
Saute for 2 minutes until shrimp turn pink. Remove with slotted spoon.
Melt remaining margarine; add green onions and tarragon and saute for 3 minutes.
Add rum, stirring constantly to deglaze and cook for 30 seconds.
Return shrimp to pan with any extra liquid and cook for 1 minute or until hot. Serve over yellow rice.

title: dried peach cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add others.
This will be thin.
Pour into 3 prepared pans and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamed beans and potatoes
directions: Drain green beans, potatoes and mushrooms. Cut potatoes into chunks.
Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour.
Beat in milk, basil, salt, rosemary and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add vegetables and heat through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and corn syrup together 2 minutes in microwave.
Stir in vanilla and powdered sugar.
Add Rice Krispies; mix until well coated.
Spread on greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Fold in cottage cheese, sour cream and onion.
Set aside.
Cook meat until no longer pink; drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheesy onion burger buns
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast and butter.
Add hot water gradually.
Beat two minutes.
Add 1 cup flour; beat two minutes.
Stir in cheese, onions and remaining flour.
Knead.
Let rise about one hour.
Punch down.
Divide into 20 pieces.
Shape into buns.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: lake norman catfish stew
directions: Thaw frozen fillets and remove skin.
Cut fillets into 1-inch pieces.
Fry bacon until lightly browned in a large kettle over low heat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, corn, peas, catsup and seasonings.
Bring to the boiling point.
Reduce heat and cook covered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add fish and continue cooking for 40 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 10 servings.

title: delicious meatballs
directions: Mix together well the first 6 ingredients; shape into balls. Fry in electric skillet; drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs in skillet.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain fruits and use juice as the part of cold water.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: meatballs
directions: In an electric skillet at 300°, mix chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice.
Let simmer until mix becomes a sauce.
Mix together hamburger, egg, salt, pepper and fine grated onion.
Roll into meatballs.
Let stand in sauce about 10 minutes, turning often.

title: blender coconut cream pie
directions: Combine in blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix until smooth.
Place dip in center of serving tray and arrange fresh vegetables around same.

title: chili rellenos(stuffed peppers)
directions: Mix eggs and water.
Heat peppers on dry skillet until skin is partially brown.
Peel skin off peppers and cut about 1/2-inch on side of pepper.
Remove seeds and stuff with cheese.
Close and dip in egg batter.
Place in hot oil until brown.
Add salt to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add sugar and butter.
Spread in the bottom of a pan (or casserole).
Chill in refrigerator for about an hour.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, milk and whipped topping.
Spread on top of chilled graham crackers.
Cut strawberries into halves and place on whipped topping nicely and snugly.
Follow the quick set method on the side of the Jell-O package.
After the Jell-O is almost thickened, pour on top of the strawberries.
Chill until Jell-O is firm.
Since the Strawberry Delight gets watery at the bottom, quickly eat all in one day.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth. Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top of center of chicken mixture.
Twist slightly and seal edges. Brush with melted butter and top with crushed croutons.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Pour salt over cracklings;
mix well.
Add meal and hot water to make
a	stiff
paste.
Make 2 pones and bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: marshmallow krispie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare and bake brownies following package directions for original.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle marshmallows on hot brownies and return to oven.
Bake for 3 minutes. Combine the chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in medium saucepan. Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted.
Add rice cereal and mix well. Spread mixture over marshmallow layer. Refrigerate until chilled. Cut in bars.
Yields 24 bars.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Stir-fry the ingredients in a large skillet.
Add 1/4 cup cooking sherry if desired (or can flavor with soy sauce).

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and arrange in casserole dish.
Top with cubed, cooked chicken breasts.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar together in a large mixing bowl.
Beat the eggs until light and add to the mixture.
Thoroughly mash the bananas with a fork to make about 1 cup.
Fold the bananas gently into butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and soda together and add to the mixture.
Flour the pecans and add last, stirring gently with a wooden spoon.
Spread the batter evenly in a greased loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake for 1 hour; allow to cool slightly before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops from peppers and remove seeds and membranes.
Cook for 4 or 5 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Combine meat with the next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Stuff into peppers.
Combine all of the other ingredients to make a sauce and pour over peppers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for an hour or until done.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix first ten ingredients and put into large casserole dish. Top with cheese and crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Bake pie shells and cool.
Mix all other ingredients together. Pour into pie shell.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: jr.'s spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook noodles; drain.
Mix beef mixture, sauce and noodles together.
Top with cheese.

title: peanut butter ripple fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart bowl on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave 5 minutes on High or until mixture comes to a full rolling boil, stirring thoroughly after 3 minutes.
Mix well.
Continue microwaving 5 1/2 minutes, mixing well and scraping sides of bowl after 3 minutes. Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cut through fudge with knife for marble effect.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: five cup salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl, adding sour cream last.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: wassette casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet with vegetables, salt and chili powder. Drain off excess fat.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix meat over mixture of cream of mushroom soup and noodles.
Pour into large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cheese on top.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook chopped spinach and large diced onion together and drain. Add Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 pound of diced pepperoni, diced black olives, 1 Tbsp. oil and dash of garlic powder.
Put mixture in pie shell.
Top with 2nd crust and seal.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger with meat loaf mix.
Peel potatoes, dice in medium pieces, parboil and place around meat loaf.
Pour soup over meat and potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Saute broccoli, margarine, onions and mushrooms, then add soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed, then add sour cream and Cool Whip. In deep dish, layer pudding, crumbled vanilla wafers and chopped up bananas until gone.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: shoo-fly coffee cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Reserve 1/3 cup of crumbs. Stir together hot water and molasses.
Add to crumb mixture; stir until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, sugar and egg.
Add buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients together. Combine and mix well both mixtures. Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Chill dough for 1 hour. Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on slightly greased baking sheet. Top each cookie with a cherry or a nut. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Mix the remainder of the ingredients together with the sugar and Crisco.
Roll into balls, size of walnut, and dip in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Cookies will rise, fall and crack.
Chill dough for easy handling.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in a casserole dish.
Top with onion soup and cheese in that order.
Mix dressing with margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Grease a cake pan.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in the next 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and sugar is completely dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until temperature reaches 260° or until a hard but plastic ball is formed in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flavoring oil and food coloring.
Pour into cake pan.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Grease hands and pull until it has a satin-like finish and light color.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in wax paper. Makes about 1 pound.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put cranapple juice and apple juice or cider into clean 30-cup coffeepot.
In basket add brown sugar, cinnamon and whole cloves. Perk just like coffee.

title: white chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil or bake chicken breasts, shred by hand or with food processor and set aside.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Combine butter, garlic and herb mix. Butter well one side of each piece of bread. Next, generously spread the same side with the cream cheese. Place on a foil-lined baking sheet and liberally top with the grated cheese. Bake in the upper level of a 400° oven until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach quiche
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, over very low heat, melt margarine. Whisk in salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix egg and milk; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in cheeses, spinach and onion.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: ron's baby back ribs
directions: Cut slabs into 4 bone sections and boil on stove top until thoroughly browned, then pour off water.
Mix salt, pepper, barbecue sauce, ketchup, syrup and ribs in a large bowl until meat is covered then bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes in baking pans.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: In one bowl mix flour and baking soda.
In another bowl mix butter and sugars.
In a third bowl mix the vanilla and pudding.

title: marinade steak
directions: Mix soy sauce with the brown sugar, pepper and olive oil.
Pour into a shallow pan.
Put steak in the sauce and spoon a little sauce over top.
Marinate for 30 minutes, turning several times. Heat a large, heavy skillet.
Cook the steak over high heat until very brown; turn and cook quickly until very brown.
Steak will be almost charred on the outside and pink in the middle.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
You can freeze them.

title: fajita marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients in plastic container.
Pierce flank steak, or venison steak, thoroughly with a fork.
Place in marinade and refrigerate overnight.
Turn meat every 3 or 4 hours to marinate evenly.
Meat can be cooked on grill or under your broiler.
Serve on warmed flour tortillas with sauteed onions and peppers, shredded cheese, sour cream, salsa and guacamole.
(I substitute white wine vinegar when marinating chicken breasts.)

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix chopped pecans, 4 tablespoons butter and brown sugar together and set aside.

title: viv's blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix lightly with washed, drained blackberries.
Pour in pie shell.
Place dots of butter all over fruit.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.

Roll out the other pie crust and cut with a knife in 1/2-inch strips and place across the pie. Pinch the ends of the dough at the outside rim of the pie. Crisscross the dough strips to form a lattice effect.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of sugar.
Place the cobbler in a foil-lined pan and bake in preheated 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: date delights
directions: Combine sugar, butter, egg, dates and pecans in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat until well blended, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cereal.
Let cool.
With buttered hands, roll in 1-inch balls; roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: "red hot" jello salad
directions: Put Jell-O in cooking pan.
Add water and stir until dissolved. Add red hots and put over heat.
Stir until red hots are dissolved. Add applesauce.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and serve.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 2 well-greased 1 quart molds, filling a little more than half full.
Cover with foil. Set molds on rack in deep kettle and add boiling water to come halfway up sides of molds.
Cover and steam for 2 1/2 hours. Replace boiling water to keep up level of liquid.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and powdered sugar with margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together the eggs, sugar, 1/2 cup flour, salt and rhubarb.
Pour over the crust and bake at 350° an additional 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: seafood curry
directions: Cook onion in oil until transparent.
Blend in flour and curry.
Add soup and cook gently until sauce is heated.
Mix in seafood, sherry and sour cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot over fluffy cooked rice.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: beef 'n' beans
directions: Saute ground beef and onion; drain off grease and combine beef, onion, beans and barbecue sauce and heat.
Ingredients can of course be varied to taste.
This is a great outdoor meal for hearty eaters.

title: pasta al cavolfiore
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a deep, heavy skillet.
Add crushed garlic, bay leaf and basil.
Saute one minute, then add cauliflower and sprinkle it with one teaspoon salt.
Saute until cauliflower is tender.
You might want to add some water (1/2 to 1 cup) to steam it along.
When cauliflower is tender, add tomato puree and lower to a simmer.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: sylvia glover's clam dip
directions: Mince and simmer until soft onion, garlic, butter, parsley, oregano, Tabasco and pepper.
Simmer clams and lemon juice for 15 minutes.
Mix two mixtures together and add 1/2 cup Italian breadcrumbs.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Pour into baking dish (optional, top with Cheddar cheese).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400° uncovered.

title: miami creamy chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine Thousand Island dressing, turkey or chicken, celery,
cucumber, onion and green pepper.
Gently fold in oranges.
Cover	and
chill.
To
serve,
line serving dish with lettuce, then spoon on salad mixture.	Makes about 6 servings.

title: sloppy sandwiches
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add last 3 to meat and mix.
Make sandwiches and warm in oven until cheese melts, approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Add veggies and seasonings.
Heat and serve with taco chips.

title: banana medley ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan. Gradually stir in cream. Bring to boil, stirring constantly, over low heat; simmer 2 minutes. Add small amount of hot mixture to egg mixture. Mix well. Add egg mixture to remaining hot mixture. Simmer on low heat 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add bananas, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix well. Pour in freezer. Follow manufacturer's directions. Makes 2 quarts.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: To pie filling, add 3 bananas.
Mix, coating bananas.
Add 3 more bananas and mix well.
(This will keep bananas from turning brown.)
Add other ingredients, mix well.
Chill and serve.
Add nuts or other fruit, if desired.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Spread nuts and coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix with eggs, water and oil.
Pour over coconut. Heat cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: cherry nut crunch
directions: Arrange ingredients in order listed (except for margarine). Melt margarine and spoon over top.
Be sure to cover entire dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least an hour to blend flavors.
This is good with carrot and celery sticks, cauliflower, broccoli, cucumbers and apple slices that have been dipped in lemon juice to keep them from turning brown.
Low-fat or light (lite) mayonnaise may be used.
This will keep in the refrigerator several weeks.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine over low-heat, slowly until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add box of sugar.
Work fast to mix and blend.
Pour and spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Spoon into 12 hole greased muffin tin, filling almost to top.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: spanakopita (spinach pie)
directions: Let filo thaw out thoroughly before opening or it will stick together.
Thaw out spinach and squeeze out all the water you can.
(You can cook and chop an equivalent amount of fresh spinach, but it's a big pain and it won't taste any different.)

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla; fold in Cool Whip.

title: lottie moon's sugar biscuits
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop with spoon (far apart) on cookie sheet and bake at 475° until done.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, ginger and garlic powder. Cover chicken breasts with marinade and refrigerate for 24 hours. Grill until done.
Lightly grill pineapple slices.
Top each chicken breast with a pineapple slice.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Saute pepper, onions and mushrooms.
In a very large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be cooked in the microwave.

title: oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Sift flour, soda, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add uncooked oatmeal and mix well.
This recipe makes 8 dozen.

title: apple squash soup
directions: Bake squash at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Halve and remove pulp and seeds. Combine remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes. Add squash. Blend well in blender. Reheat before serving. Garnish with parsley.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery; drain.
Add rest of ingredients but beans.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Add beans and simmer again.
May add tomato paste, water and a dash of sugar to taste. Makes 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; mold into meatballs and brown in oil. Mix sugar, water and vinegar; pour over meatballs. Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Pare potatoes
and cook until tender, 30 to 35 minutes. Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp. Remove and
drain.
Cook
and
stir
chopped
onion
in
bacon drippings until
tender
and	golden.
Stir
in
flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook very slowly over low heat, stirring until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove the
skillet
from heat.
Crumble the bacon and slice the potatoes.
Carefully stir the bacon and potatoes into the
hot mixture in the skillet.
Heat through, stirring lightly to coat the potato slices.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, 15 minutes at 375° and 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk until thick like paste on stove.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Whip shortening, sugar, almond extract and flour in bowl until thick like whipped cream.
Spread over cake.
Keep cake in refrigerator to keep from separating.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in covered container.

title: russian tea
directions: Make syrup and boil 15 minutes.
Mix all together.
Serve hot.

title: coconut and black walnut cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk. Roll nuts in flour.
Stir in nuts, coconut and extract.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Pour hot coconut syrup over warm cake.
Allow cake to remain in pan for 4 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: To each pound of cabbage, add 2 teaspoons of salt.
Mix thoroughly, only 4 to 6 pounds at a time.
Mix good and pack tightly in jars.
Put lids on loosely.
Put in plastic or enamel containers to ferment.
Set in a cool place for 10 days, then make a brine of 2 tablespoons of salt to 1 quart of water and refill jars.
Wash lids good so they will seal.
Fill jars so they are full.
Process 30 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Drop by tablespoon or more on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool on cookie sheet.
These are supposed to be large cookies (usually 6 on a cookie sheet).

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and 2 1/2 cups warm water.
Add the flour and let rise. Roll out dough; spread with butter, cinnamon, sugar, nuts and raisins.
Roll up and cut into 1 1/4-inch slices; let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Glaze, if desired.

title: grandma's holiday sausage
directions: Combine beef with water, mixing well.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except pepper. Form beef mixture into 1 or 2 logs, roll in pepper.
Wrap logs in aluminum foil; refrigerate for 24 hours. Prepare for baking by punching holes in bottom of foil and place on broiler pan with 1/4 inch water in bottom of pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on wire rack and refrigerate for easier slicing.
Serve with cheese and crackers.
Serve with sweet and spicy mustard for tart taste.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: six layer cookies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer ingredients in order.
Evenly spread each layer.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely (or chill in refrigerator).
Cut into bars.

title: mud hen and  icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add two whole eggs and yolks of other 2 eggs (save white for icing). Sift in dry ingredients and mix. Add vanilla. Grease and flour 9 X 12 inch pan. Pour batter into pan. Add chopped pecans on top of batter.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan greased with oil.
Bake at 450° for 50 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cube.
Spread chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Melt margarine and crush Ritz crackers in it.
Sprinkle over casserole, then sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except noodles and peas.
Add these just before serving.
Great served on lettuce leaf with fruit and a hot roll.

title: greek tuna salad
directions: Gently combine the first 8 ingredients (through the oregano) in a large bowl. Season lightly with salt and pepper. Drizzle 1 cup of the olive oil and 1/2 cup of the vinegar over the salad and toss gently. The ingredients should only be coated lightly with the oil and vinegar. Add a little more of each and gently toss again. Serve with crisp lettuce greens, if desired.

title: holiday pumpkin pie
directions: Brush crust with some of the beaten egg.
Bake at 400° for 4 minutes.
Set aside.
In bowl blend pumpkin, remaining eggs, half and half or light cream, granulated sugar, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice and ginger until smooth.
Divide and pour filling into prepared crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack. Garnish with whipped topping and pecan halves, if desired.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine sugar and soda in 3-quart saucepan; mix well. Stir in cream. Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook and stir to soft-ball stage (234°). (Mixture caramelizes slightly as it cooks.) Remove from heat; add butter. Stir in pecans; beat until thick enough to drop from spoon (takes only 2 or 3 minutes). Drop from tablespoon on waxed paper. If candy becomes too stiff to drop, add a tablespoon of hot water. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: savory rice
directions: Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.
Stir once after the oleo melts. Don't cover.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Drain carrots and combine all ingredients except sugar and butter.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish and add ingredients. Sprinkle sugar and butter on top and cover.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan; sprinkle with brown sugar. Arrange apples, overlapping wedges on sugar.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla together.
Add egg and beat vigorously.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour; cool 5 minutes, then turn upside down on a serving plate.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy. Add beaten egg yolks.
Sift all the dry ingredients and add alternately with the molasses and water in which soda was dissolved.
Beat egg whites and fold them gently into the other mixture.
Bake in a 14 x 9-inch or 11 x 8-inch baking dish or pan. Grease and flour pan/dish.
If using pan, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If using baking dish, reduce the oven temperature to 325°.
Good served alone or with whipped topping or a lemon sauce.

title: government dinner
directions: Cook vegetables; drain well.
In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: emma's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt together.
Add 3 egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat and beat in butter and vanilla.
Let cool, then pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until they peak.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and beat again.
Place on top of pie and cook until brown. Very easy and good!

title: light barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, partially covered, for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer until warm. Set aside.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, soup, mayonnaise and eggs.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix crackers in butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms in chicken broth with celery, then add chicken and mushrooms; also minced onion, green pepper and pimento, if desired.
Season to taste and cook 20 minutes.

title: quick preserves
directions: Use any fresh fruit in season or frozen fruit:
peaches, blackberries, strawberries, cherries, pears, apples.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese with onion, garlic salt and enough milk to soften.
Fold in crab meat and mound on plate.
Place Ritz crackers around plate.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well. Mix
cups flour with remaining dry ingredients. Sift together.
Add
alternately with milk and first mixture. Mix blueberries
with remaining flour and fold in.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: butterhorn crescent rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water in large bowl; stir until dissolved.
Add milk, salt, sugar, 1/3 cup oleo, eggs and 1/2 of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually stir in rest of flour.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes or until light, elastic, smooth and no longer sticky.
Cover; let rise 20 minutes. Punch down; divide into 3 pieces.
Roll each into 12-inch circle. Spread with soft oleo; cut into 12 pie-shaped wedges.
Start rolling at large end and roll to point.
Place on greased baking sheet point down.
Brush with melted oleo.
Cover; let rise.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
(Can be refrigerated up to 24 hours). Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes, if refrigerated.

title: ginger lime scallops
directions: Mix room temperature butter with ginger, zest, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Dry scallops; saute until golden in oil.
Drain.
Stir in lime juice and saute 1 minute.
Lower heat and add butter mixture one tablespoon until sauce thickens. Stir in nuts and sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: chili dog pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine baking mix, mustard and water in a small bowl.
Stir until dough forms.
Press dough into bottom and up sides of dish.
Set aside.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour into casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Serves 8. Can be doubled. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: homemade cracker jack
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add flavoring and soda.
Stir into corn and nuts.
Spread in large pan (roaster works best) and bake at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Store in can to keep crisp.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip until creamy and smooth; chill.
Serve with fresh strawberries, bananas, pineapple or your own favorites!

title: s'mores
directions: Toast 1 or 2 marshmallows; place piece of chocolate bar on graham cracker.
Place toasted marshmallows on chocolate and put another graham cracker on top.
The heat of the marshmallows will melt the chocolate and it will be all squishy and good.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix together in bowl; flour, salt, baking powder; then add shortening.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water; knead.
Add the other 1/2 cup boiling water, knead until it's smooth enough to roll out.
Keep in one big ball of dough; then make from dough form the size of golf balls.
Roll out.
Cook at low to medium heat on a griddle or skillet, turn until done.

title: mamma's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together until thoroughly blended.
Shape into golf ball size meatballs.
Place onto a greased pan into an oven preheated to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove them from the pan and put them in your favorite red pasta sauce.
Let simmer for 2 hours on low heat.
Serve with pasta.
Not recommended for cooking ahead and/or freezing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french silk chocolate pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Keep beating and add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each one.
Add pecans and pour in baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: devil's food cake supreme
directions: Cook cake mix as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and punch holes over entire cake with fork.
Pour milk and ice cream topping over cake.
Refrigerate until cool.
Top with Cool Whip.
Finally, top with Heath bars or your favorite candy bar.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chips and milk together in a heavy pan, stirring often. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Also, add nuts, if desired. When fully mixed, press into 9 x 12-inch pan lined with waxed paper or drop small amounts in fluted paper candy cups. Refrigerate until firm.
If in pan, turn out onto cutting board and cut into desired size pieces.
Can be frozen.

title: crowd pleaser potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave.
Let cool and cut into cubes, leaving skins on.
Melt other ingredients in pan on top of stove. Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked cod fillets
directions: Sprinkle fish fillets with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and slowly pour over fish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 2.

title: chicken paprikash(hungarian recipe)
directions: Melt shortening in heavy pan; brown onion.
Add chicken, paprika, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add water to cover.
Cover tightly and cook slowly until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes to an hour.
Mix flour with sour cream (and milk if desired) to form a paste; add to chicken and stir well.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Add pecans, salt and pepper.
Mix in flour.
Roll out into a log and chill overnight. Slice thin and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: john's homemade pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Beat vigorously and then knead.
Let the dough rest for 5 minutes. Then pat and spread the dough on a lightly greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Spread with your favorite pizza sauce and toppings. Bake at 425° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes the sugar, one orange rind half, cloves and five cups of water.
Strain and cool.
Bring the 8 cups of water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover and allow to steep at least 5 minutes.
Mix together tea, syrup and fruit juices.
Keep warm, but do not boil.
Serves 25.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Mix together the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter; place in microwave until melted.
Add the marshmallows and peanuts; mix.
Spread the mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm; cut into squares.

title: fred's dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese; gradually beat in powdered sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip as on box.
Mix 1 cup Dream Whip with cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cooled crust. Prepare pudding and cool.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Spread can of cherry pie filling over pudding and put on rest of Dream Whip. Spread coconut on top.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch. Add beaten egg yolks, butter and boiling water. Cook until thick. Put in baked pie shell. Cover with meringue. Bake in oven at 350° until egg whites are brown.

title: potatoes paprika
directions: Peel potatoes and cut as for French fries.
Heat oil in a large saucepan and add onion and garlic.
Cook gently until onion is transparent.
Stir in the paprika and potatoes.
Season with salt and cook for a few seconds while stirring.
Add the water, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the bell pepper and tomato. Cover and simmer until potatoes are just tender (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
Serve with mild Polish or Italian sausage.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into three greased tin cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir butter, eggs, peanut butter, flour and add a dab of salt. Get out a pan and a spoon.
You take the spoon and dip the spoon in the bowl.
Fill the spoon with the peanut butter cookies and put it on the pan.
Fill the pan with peanut butter cookies and poot them in the oven at 200 degrees for 40 minutes.
Take them out to cool. Enjoy!

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 3 items in a baking dish.
Mix crackers and butter together; spread over other items in dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: no bean dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in a round 1-inch deep glass pan.
Pour Hormel chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Put in 350° oven until hot and cheese melts or use microwave oven.
Serve with Mexican chips.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp in large pot of boiling water 3 to 4 minutes until pink and firm.
Drain and cool immediately under cold water; drain well.
In a large bowl (not aluminum), mix lime juice, salt, pepper, bay leaves and cumin seed.
Cover and chill overnight. Discard bay leaves.
Makes 12 appetizer servings.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Dip each piece of bread in melted butter and put in baking dish. Combine sugar, tomato puree and juice.
Heat to boiling point.
Pour over bread.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: linguica surprise
directions: Slice and dice the onion and green pepper; fry in saucepan until nice and brown.
Next, cut up the linguica into bite size pieces.
Add it to the pepper and onion.
Cook until well done, approximately 10 minutes.
Boil the 4 cups of water with the salt. When water comes to a boil, add your rice and cover.
Remove from flame; let sit approximately 5 minutes.
Pour rice into serving dish and pour linguica mixture over it.
Add ketchup and mix well. May salt and pepper to taste.
Yields about eight 1/2-cup servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix together.
Cook, uncovered, 2 to 3 hours.

title: purple cow jumped over the moon
directions: Place yogurt, milk, grape juice concentrate and lemon juice in food processor or blender; process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: veal
directions: Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Push to side of pan and brown veal cutlets on both sides.
Add cream of mushroom soup. Cover cutlet with mixture and cook over medium heat about 15 minutes.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend ingredients, then add shrimp.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: You may cook them in peanut oil or, after you cook your fish, cook them in the leftover oil.

title: working girl biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add eggs and oil.
Add sugar and flour (may use more or less flour).
Roll out on floured cutting board.
Cut or pinch into rolls, then put in a greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: lemon marinated beef steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except steak, to make marinade.
Coat entire surface of steak.
Place in shallow baking dish; let stand several hours in refrigerator.
Turn occasionally.
Cook steak over hot coals on outdoor grill.

title: crock-pot italian sauce
directions: Mix all together with hands.
Shape into 10 medium size balls. Brown in 5 tablespoons oil.
Transfer to sauce in crock-pot.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and spread.
Add in layers, in order, all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Quick, easy and yummy!

title: jerky
directions: Cut meat in 1/4-inch thick strips, 4 to 5-inches long.
Mix liquids and seasonings together, then put meat in.
Stir once in a while. Press meat down again.
Marinate 2 days.
Take out and drain. Hang the strips on oven racks, oven 120° to 140°.
Put potholder between door and oven to open a little.
Keep in 6 hours.
Test it; sometimes it takes longer.
Put cookie sheet underneath to catch drippings.

title: eggplant pancakes
directions: Cook eggplant until tender.
Squeeze all water out.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Set aside.

title: quick mix cookies
directions: Mix all together; drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken pasta primavera
directions: Cook and stir broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil on medium heat (about 10 minutes).
Stir in chicken, salt and tomatoes (about 3 minutes).
Spoon chicken over hot macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a bowl. Heat butter, coke, and cocoa to boiling point and pour over flour mixture. Mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla, and marshmallows. Bake in sheet cake pan 30-35 minutes at 350.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Add tomato soup, catsup, salt and pepper; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on warm bun halves; sprinkle with cheese.
(Mixture freezes well.)

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash sweet potatoes and add sugar, melted margarine, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Blend with mixer until smooth.
Pour into one deep dish or 2 small pie shells.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: marinated beef tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in shallow baking dish on heavy plastic storage bag.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well. Pour over tenderloin.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours, turning beef several times.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place in roasting pan in 450° oven.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Roast for 30 minutes or to desired degree of doneness.
Let stand on serving platter for several minutes before slicing.

title: vegetable pasta
directions: Boil linguine according to package.
Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Cut carrots in strips.
Cut up mushrooms.
Steam each separately (broccoli, carrots and string beans).

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: *You can use peaches, pineapple, etc., but it must be drained.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and butter.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: turtle nut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: spinach  dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach. Mix
sour cream, mayonnaise, and Knorr mix. Add thawed spinach. Mix well. Chill. Serve with sour dough bread.

title: anne's cake
directions: Combine cheese, sugar and eggs. Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Decorate with fresh fruit or berries. Refrigerate.
Stays fresh and moist.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 30 seconds in blender or 1 minute by hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate.

title: italian cake
directions: Cream the butter and the sugar for 10 minutes.
Mix the dry ingredients with the flour and add slowly to the creamed butter along with the other ingredients.
Put in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake for 1 hour in a slow oven (325°).

title: zucchini cabbage stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a wok.
Add garlic; brown and discard.
Add vegetables and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add seasonings.
Reduce heat and continue stirring 5 to 6 minutes, until vegetables are cooked, but still crisp.
Serves 6.

title: salmon pasta salad
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones, if desired.
Break into large pieces.
In medium bowl, combine salmon with pasta, carrots, celery, olives, onions, pepper and cheese.
Separately, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour over salmon mixture.
Toss carefully to coat.
Cover and chill or serve immediately.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Cream sour cream and cream cheese.
Add Tabasco sauce and taco sauce.
Stir in the beans and all but 3 tablespoons of the cheese. Put in an oven-proof serving bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet-sour pot roast
directions: Heat shortening in Dutch oven or heavy skillet with tight-fitting lid. Add meat and onions; brown, turning frequently. Add pepper, cloves, honey, sugar, lemon juice and salt. Cover tightly. Simmer slowly over low heat or bake in 300° oven 3 to 3 1/2 hours until meat is tender.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until vegetables are done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 1-quart casserole dish.
In medium saucepan, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of the cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: stir-fry casserole
directions: Brown meat in teriyaki in the wok or electric frypan.
Add spice mix (mixed with water).
Add vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Serve on cooked rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift ingredients and add to first mixture.
Then add nuts and apples.
(May have to mix by hand.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan.

title: easy chip dip
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least two hours.

title: potato-sausage bake
directions: Spread hash browns in baking sheet. Brown sausage and drain. Spread over hash browns. Spread shredded cheese over sausage. Beat eggs; add salt and paprika. Add milk and mix well. Pour mixture over hash browns, sausage and cheese. Cover with foil. Bake at 350 degrees oven for about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: old fashioned coleslaw
directions: Scoop out the center section of the cabbage, leaving only a shell.
Shred remaining cabbage and soak in ice water for 30 minutes.
Drain and dry thoroughly.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and set aside. Dissolve sugar in cold water and bring to a quick boil. Add Jell-O mixture and let cool. Add lemon and pineapple juice. Mix and freeze in 2 ice cream buckets. Thaw 1 to 2 hours before serving. Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: oven smoked turkey
directions: Grease a large brown paper grocery bag well with vegetable oil and set aside.
Preheat oven to bake at 350°.
Wash turkey and pat dry.
Combine all of the ingredients together to form a paste.
Rub the turkey well with the paste, inside and out.
Place the turkey in the greased bag, tying bag with a string.
Place on a broiler pan and roast at 350° for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and let stand at room temperature for at least 30 minutes before opening bag.
Remove turkey and carve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in fat.
Add chili powder, salt, catsup and water.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Add beans and simmer for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; put into Pyrex dish.
Grind orange.
Mix together.
Pour over the 2 cups sugar and let set.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water; let set.
Dissolve the lemon Jell-O in boiling water, then add cold water.
Mix all together in Pyrex dish.
Let set at least 10 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: molded beet salad
directions: Drain beets and save juice, adding water to make 2 cups.
Pour into saucepan with jello, sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and salt. Cook until all is dissolved and then cool.
Meanwhile, dice celery and beets.
Grate onion.
Mix in cool gelatin and place in 9 x 13-inch dish or 8 x 12-inch dish.
Cool until solid.
Serve on lettuce.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes and either cut in small pieces or shred.
Spread butter around in large casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients and put in dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: out-of-this-world cake
directions: Mix. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour crushed pineapple and juice over cake.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese or vanilla frosting and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: hudson's sesame dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice.
Stir thoroughly.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly, and continue until thick.
Add sesame seed.
Beat for 1 minute (use electric beater) at a medium speed.
Store in a cool place.

title: sorrel soup
directions: Boil potatoes, sorrel and leek in water or broth.
Place in blender when cool.
Add cream and salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken breasts deluxe
directions: Arrange chicken in a 2-quart, buttered baking dish.
Combine soups and sherry.
Stir in cheese and green onion.
Pour over chicken breasts.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender
and	save
1 1/2 cups broth. Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix
soup,
mayonnaise, cheese and 1 cup chicken broth together.
Layer
broccoli in bottom of long dish. Layer chicken next.
Pour
soup
mixture
over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing
mix
on top.
Moisten lightly with balance of chicken broth.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: egg pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on top of stove until thickened. Pour into pie shell or loaf pan.
Beat egg whites.
Pour on top. Bake in medium oven until brown.

title: rainbow finger gelatin
directions: For gelatin mixture:
Mix each box of flavored gelatin separately with 1 envelope unflavored gelatin and 1 cup hot water. Pour 1 flavored gelatin mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Place drained broccoli in oblong baking dish.
Mix milk, chestnuts and soup together. Pour over broccoli.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken soup for one
directions: In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Add carrot and onion. Cook, stirring frequently, 4 to 5 minutes until tender.
Stir in flour and black pepper.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, broth, packet and basil; bring to boil.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in boiling water. Cream cheese and vinegar until smooth. Mix all together and chill. Make a day before use.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, not soft; drain.
Grease casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and Velveeta cheese.
Add mixture to the broccoli.
Melt 1 stick of butter and add to crackers. Spread mixture over broccoli.
Heat for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix by hand.
Grease and flour loaf pans. Pour mixture into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cooked, let it cool completely before cutting.

title: farfelle
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water according to package directions.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put yolks in a greased 1 1/2-quart bowl and beat.
Add all other ingredients.
Fold in egg whites last; dot with butter.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sarah's stuffed manicotti
directions: Thaw, cook and drain spinach and place in large mixing bowl. Fry and crumble sausage; drain.
Mix with spinach.
Mix cottage cheese and slightly beaten eggs with spinach and sausage mix and set aside.
Add manicotti shells to boiling water; stir occasionally until shells are still a little hard (3 to 5 minutes).
Drain.
Pour enough sauce to cover bottom of 10 x 14-inch baking dish.
Stuff each shell with sausage mix and place in baking dish in rows; not on top of each other.
Pour remaining sauce over shells and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place in preheated oven, 400°, and bake for 45 minutes covered until sauce bubbles and cheese melts.
This doubles well and is even better leftover.

title: denise's danish
directions: Roll out one puff pastry sheet to about 6 x 12-inches. Transfer to baking sheet.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados and blend with sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: wacky cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa. Add oil, vinegar, water and vanilla. Blend well with dry ingredients. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan until toothpick comes clean when tested.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan.
Pour batter in.
Cook 55 to 65 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrot, squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 3/4 of stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 8-inch pan or serving dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.

title: wellesley fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup of the sugar; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Cool.
Mix flour, soda and salt. Cream butter.
Gradually beat in remaining 1 1/4 cups sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in centers comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on racks.
Spread desired frosting between layers and over top and sides.
Garnish with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: scripture cake(this comes from a mountain cookbook.)
directions: Select a nice, kind, amiable, industrious and generous man and prepare him for the ordeal of making him go through a long engagement, which effectually renders him easy to handle.

title: eggless cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together.
Add 1 cup of flour at a time.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Measure by teaspoon and drop on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: saucy chicken and pasta dinner
directions: Heat 1/4 cup of the Parkay spread in a large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic powder; cook 4 minutes. Stir in remaining 1/4 cup Parkay spread, mushrooms and peas; cook 2 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in hot cooked noodles and cheese until cheese is melted.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low fat potato soup
directions: Mix broth and gravy in crockpot and stir well.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Mix pecans, egg, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla until smooth. Fill each pastry shell 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove immediately and cool on rack.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Place alternate layers of chicken, tortillas, onion and peppers in casserole. Add the soup, undiluted.
Put tomatoes over this.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken

title: beef bourguignon(beef burgundy)
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon crisply and remove to large platter.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil; set aside.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients, then add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Put in prepared sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Frost immediately!

title: flitch
directions: Mix together by hand.
Add enough milk to form a dough like consistency.
Roll out like pie dough.
Use more 10x sugar when rolling to keep from sticking.
Spread entire jar of peanut butter over dough and roll up.
Chill, slice and serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions with wine and butter.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with sour dough slices.
Spread parmesan cheese over slices of bread.

title: rock candy
directions: Heat water until it just starts to boil.
Continue gentle heating, add sugar gradually and stir until all sugar has dissolved.
Keep on stirring.
Carefully pour into a tall jar.
Tie string to pen or pencil and tie paper clip at other end.
Tie so paper clip almost touches bottom.
Dip the string in solution. Roll the string in dry sugar so that sugar sticks to string. Return string to solution and let it stand undisturbed (3 to 10 days).
Wrap up in whatever you want for Christmas.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer until soft.
Pour in Eagle Brand milk. Add lemon juice and vanilla. Blend until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours for hardening. Cover with cherries.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Melt butter and mix with corn flakes.
Layer hash browns in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour on soup; mix. Layer on cheese, then corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese and egg spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and use as a spread on buttered toast or crackers.

title: susan's famous fat-free bean soup
directions: *If you prefer, chop the celery and bell pepper finely and leave in the soup.
I just prefer the flavor, not the ingredients.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: creamed leeks
directions: Heat margarine in a skillet and add the leeks.
Cook, covered, for 3 minutes.
Add the milk and reduce until the liquid disappears.
Per serving: 85 calories, 1 mg cholesterol, 2 g fat, 30 mg sodium.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: grandma's chili
directions: Saute onions; brown meat, then mix in all remaining ingredients to heat thoroughly.
Season to taste.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: frozen blueberry yogurt
directions: Cook blueberries and honey together for about 4 minutes; cool completely.
Place blueberry mixture in a food processor; process until thoroughly blended.
Fold in yogurt.
Freeze, then process again if smoother texture is desired.
Refreeze.
Makes 4 servings.

title: reuben salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cool.
Combine the rest of the ingredients. Add to macaroni.
Stir well and chill.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water in saucepan.
Turn heat low and add flour and salt all at once, stirring vigorously, until mixture leaves sides of pan in a smooth, compact mass.
Remove from heat. Quickly beat in eggs, one at a time, beating mixture until smooth and stiff.
Drop by heaping tablespoons 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet, shaping into rounds with point in center, using a wet spoon.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then at 400° for 20 minutes.
Fill with whipped cream or pudding.

title: pink punch
directions: Put cherries and bananas in a blender and make pulp.
Put in gallon container and add mixed jello and juices.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Add ginger ale and sherbet.
You could use strawberries and strawberry jello.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta to package directions, rinse with cold water and drain.
In large bowl stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 10 cups salad.

title: karen's spinach pie
directions: Saute bacon to golden brown in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Add spinach and cook for 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add avocet and cook for 2 minutes.
Add butter and mix together.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to spinach pie. Mix together.
Transfer spinach pie to a casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake in oven at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Boil until tender, about 3 minutes.
Strain and bring juice to a hard boil.
Add Certo and food coloring.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peppers.
Pour into jars and seal.
This is delicious on peas, beans, meats or cheese and crackers.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat in sour cream.
Add flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and vanilla.
Put 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with pie filling, then top with remaining batter.

title: stir-fry
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in large skillet.
Add frozen stir-fry vegetables.
Stir and steam 10 minutes over medium heat. Add salt and pepper to taste, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and teriyaki.
(Do not overcook vegetables.)

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake
mix, margarine and 1 egg and pour into bottom of a greased
pan.
Mix	cream
cheese,	3
eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar
and pour over first layer.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pecans and coconut into pan; set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to package.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
In a separate bowl, cream together the cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla; drop by spoonfuls over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: *Optional:
Use 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon butter flavor.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes or until done.

title: pickles 'n bucket
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Put all others in bucket. Pour liquid over and let stand 2 days.
Split hot peppers, then refrigerate.
Once bucket lid is closed, do not open for 2 months.

title: green punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; pour over ice in punch bowl. Lime sherbet may be used instead of ice.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: parmesan meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients together lightly.
Shape into about 5 or 6 loaf shaped patties, not too flat.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Remove to platter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and slice stuffed olives. These freeze very well and are great to have on hand so double or triple the recipe.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Stir in flour until smooth. Add salmon-milk liquid.
Cook until thickened.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Drain and chop sauerkraut.
Brown sausage, ground beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients except bread crumbs and eggs. Brown.
Remove from fire; stir in bread crumbs.
Cool.
Beat 1 egg and stir in.
Form into balls.
Refrigerate or freeze balls for an hour or so to make them easier to dip.
Dip in mixture of 2 eggs and 1/4 cup milk.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place under broiler or place in 400° oven until brown and heated.

title: lemon caraway cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
