Beat the egg; add sugar and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Add shortening and caraway seed; cream thoroughly.
Add flour mixture and blend thoroughly.
Chill for several hours.

title: oh-so-easy meat pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Prepare pie crust according to package directions for two-crust pie using 9 inch pie pan. In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon mixture into pie crust. Top with second crust; flute edges. Cut slits in crust. If desired, in a small bowl, combine 1 egg yolk and 2 tsp. water; brush top of crust with egg mixture. Sprinkle with sesame or poppy seeds. Bake at 425° for 35-45 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown and filling is bubbly. Cover edge of crust with strips of foil after 15-20 minutes of baking to prevent excessive browning. Cool 10 minutes before serving. Yield: 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large casserole.
Add onion, celery and green pepper and cook on low heat until tender, but not browned.
Add soup, milk and cheese and heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Stir in drained and flaked tuna, olives, pimentos and mushrooms.
Add the noodles and stir until well mixed and no more.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: italian beef roast
directions: Saute green pepper, carrot and garlic.
Pour ingredients over meat.
Place in Dutch oven, covered.
Roast meat in 300° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Slice meat very thin when cooled.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Mix salt and flour and combine with fruit and nuts.
Mix with sugar and margarine. Drop by teaspoon (2-inches apart) on aluminum foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool before removing from foil.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen cookies.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine soups and water.
Stir in chickpeas, black beans, zucchini, carrots, chili powder, thyme and pepper.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cook 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
To serve, ladle chili into bowls.
Makes about 8 cups or 6 main dish servings. Preparation Time: 10 minutes.
Cook Time:
50 minutes.

title: kraut hot dish mushroom
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Layer ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts and filling
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Mix the soup, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Layer chicken, soup and filling.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°, or until heated.

title: butter mints
directions: Stir sugar with butter and hot water.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil in saucepan.
Cover and wait 3 minutes.
Remove lid; wash down sides of pan with a brush dipped in water.
Cook, without stirring, to 248°.
Pour onto a buttered slab; cool.
Add a few drops of vanilla and coloring; pull until candy loses its gloss. Stretch into rope and cut.

title: baked apple donuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and 1/2 cup sugar. Cut in shortening.
Add beaten egg, milk and apples all at once. Place in well-greased muffin tin.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven or until done.
Remove from pan; roll in melted butter.
Roll in cinnamon mixed with remaining sugar.

title: watermelon fruit basket
directions: Cut watermelon into shape of basket with handle.
Scoop out inside with melon scoop and set aside 4 cups of melon balls. Scoop out the insides of cantaloupe and honeydew melon and set aside 3 cups of each.
Mix all the ingredients together in large container with lid.
Refrigerate overnight to chill completely. Clean the watermelon out completely.
Pour the fruit mixture into the basket-shaped watermelon.
Decorates any summer table.
Good centerpiece for a sumer wedding or a large family get together.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in skillet.
Beat egg yolks and add eggs and milk to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium to low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into (cooked) pie crust and top with meringue.
Brown meringue at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Saute ground meat, celery and onion until meat browns.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in well-greased casserole and top with chow mein noodles.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix juice, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove and cool.
Soak eggs in juice 12 to 24 hours.
Remove from juice and serve.
Delicious anytime.

title: hye rollers
directions: Lay out tortilla shell and spread on a thin layer of cream cheese. Layer tortilla with cheese, turkey, salami, lettuce and sprinkle with onions. Roll up tortilla and seal. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap or aluminum foil. Refrigerate. When chilled slice and serve.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add remaining ingredients.
Pour half into mold; let gel.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Chop vegetables in blender.
Combine sugar, salt and vinegar. Pour this over chopped vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight. Package and freeze next day.

title: laura's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Alternate with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix all
ingredients and pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 rolls.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: In greased casserole, layer all ingredients as listed, seasoning with salt and pepper each layer.
Pour soup over all and sprinkle with garlic powder or salt.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baked chicken with curry
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Place 1/4 cup butter in 9 x 13 baking dish and melt. In plastic bag, combine 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper, paprika and curry powder; shake to blend. Add chicken, 1 piece at a time, shaking well to coat. Place in baking dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: (johnel's) cheese garlic grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
Stir in cut up cheese and margarine until melted.
Add milk to eggs and then stir into grits mixture.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend in Cool Whip. Put into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: enchilada soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Add all ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer one hour.
Add cheese and cut up tortillas. Simmer another 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: green rice
directions: Mix together in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: peanut butter frosted bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugars and soda in a large bowl.
Add oleo, peanut butter and egg.
Stir until blended well.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Center should be soft and sides beginning to pull away from the pan.
Cool completely and top with Peanut Butter Frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Cut into 18 (3 x 1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: carmel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup of the sugar in a small skillet.
Do not let it burn, just let it turn to caramel.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, milk and well beaten egg yolks.
Cook over hot water, then add caramel syrup to mixture.
Cook until thick, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
When slighly cool, cover with meringue made from 3 egg whites beaten until foamy, then beaten again with 3 Tbsp.
of sugar, added a little at a time, beaten well after each addition.
Beat until meringue is standing in peaks.
Cover the pie right to crust, making sure the meringue touches the crust and there are no gaps anywhere.
Bake in 350°oven until nicely brown.

title: miniature quiches
directions: Fry bacon in pan or fix in the microwave.
While bacon is cooking, spray 4 to 5 miniature muffin pans (1 dozen quiches per pan) with Pam.
Then take biscuits and peel apart each biscuit into at least 4 layers.
Use these to make the little crust cups for the quiches.
Then crumble the bacon; put a small piece in each cup.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese in each cup.
Whip eggs, 1 cup half and half and dash of pepper together.
Use large spoon and put 1 to 2 spoonfuls in each cup.
Then sprinkle lightly with remainder of shredded cheese.
Be careful not to overfill the cups. Rises during baking.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Watch closely since all ovens bake differently and these little quiches burn quickly!
Tastes delicious served with a fresh fruit salad for breakfast.
Makes 48 to 60 quiches.
Taste better served hot from the oven!
Also freezes well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese with electric mixer.
Add sugar and fold in the Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust.
Decorate top with more Cool Whip and shaved chocolate.
Keep in refrigerator. Can be made several days ahead.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and chilies in butter.
Add tomatoes, soup, cumin, chicken and garlic powder, if desired. Simmer 20 minutes.
Crush corn chips in blender or with rolling pin.
In a 13 x 9-inch casserole, place 1 layer of 1/3 of the corn chips and chicken mixture and top with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream topping.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil turkey leg in seasoned salt.

Dice turkey and add to broth with soup, milk and eggs. Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in oleo. Add to turkey mixture. Slowly boil; stir until thick. Add cooked spaghetti to mixture and place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with grated cheese and heat in a 350° oven until mixture begins to boil. Remove.
Serves 8.

title: dainty biscuits
directions: Mix together, spoon 2 tablespoons into small ungreased muffin pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Beat eggs and add the other ingredients and stuff turkey. When 3 hours are up, get the heck out of the kitchen because that stuffing is going to blow that turkey right out of the oven.

title: zesty guacamole dip
directions: Combine the green onions, cucumber, tomato, garlic and cilantro until well mixed. Chop the avocados into small pieces and gently combine with vegetable mixture. Squeeze lemon into mixture and season with salt, pepper and red pepper flakes to taste. Refrigerate with the avocado bits placed in the bowl until serving (this helps prevent the guacamole from turning brown).

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Let pie crust set to room temperature.
Open and drain vegetables.
Put one pie crust in a deep round casserole dish with bottom side down.
Layer on crust, chicken, soup, 1 can vegetables, celery soup, chicken (crumbled up) and can of vegetables.
Top with other crust, putting bottom side down.
Bake at 350° until crust browns.

title: corn and corned beef casserole
directions: Cook onion until tender in 1 tablespoon butter.
Combine with corned beef (broken into small pieces), potatoes, 1/2 cup evaporated milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Press against sides and bottom of shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter in skillet; blend in flour and remaining salt and pepper.
Gradually add liquid from corn and rest of milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add corn and pour into lined casserole dish.
(I spray casserole dish with Pam.)
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in moderate oven 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: swans island hot lobster spread
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.	Add all other ingredients except almonds.
Blend well.
Spoon into oven proof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 15 minutes @ 375°.

title: stuff
directions: Slice potatoes in thin slices.
Grate up cabbage.
Chop onions into small pieces.
Place ground beef in electric skillet.
Salt and pepper.
Layer potatoes, cabbage and onions.
Top with cheese. Pour undiluted mushroom soup over top.
Cook at medium heat about 10 minutes (covered).
Reduce to low and cook 20 to 30 more minutes.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine beef, rice, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into 2-inch sized balls.
Place meat balls in a baking dish.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Season with pepper to taste.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add a little additional water if necessary during cooking process.

title: chinese egg roll
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic; cook until brown.
Add onions; cook until half done.
Add tomato; cook until dissolved. Add salt, m.s.g. and pepper.
Chop shrimp in small pieces.
Add it and cook until it turns red.
Cook pork until half done.
Add celery and carrots and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Add thin sliced green beans, bean sprouts and cabbage.
Cook until done, stirring constantly to keep from burning.
Add soy sauce just before finished cooking.
The mixture should blend into a mush. Drain well before putting into wrapper.

title: white pound cake
directions: Blend all shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients and add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna and corn salad with herb bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate. Slice bread at 1-inch intervals without cutting all the way through.
Mix margarine and Italian seasoning.
Spread onto slices.
Wrap bread in foil; warm in oven for 15 minutes at 300°. Serve bread hot with salad.

title: summer cabbage salad
directions: Mix tomatoes and cabbage in large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Let chill in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Mix next 4 ingredients with mixer until smooth. Beat the eggs in one at a time.
Beat in sour cream and nuts.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Add half of the batter then half of the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Repeat process.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together and press out on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: low-fat prune bread
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Put all ingredients into the bread machine in the order listed.
Select white bread and push "Start".

title: oysters and macaroni au gratin
directions: Drain oysters.
Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Blend in flour; add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring often.
Place layer of macaroni in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover with layer of oysters.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour white sauce over contents of casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until brown around edges.
Serves 4.

title: sarah's fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch pan.
Place sugar, cocoa and butter in bowl; stir and add milk.
Heat 2 minutes at full power.
After cooking, beat with mixer until smooth, then add vanilla and nuts.
Cool 1 hour.

title: gazpacho
directions: In covered blender, blend half of the ingredients until smooth; transfer to bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients; transfer to bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time, at least 6 hours.
Ladle into chilled bowls.

title: corn dressing
directions: Mix together; put in 2-quart dish and bake at 315° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches and rum with sugar (1 cup).
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in baking dish (2-quart).
Set in oven to melt butter.
Make a batter of 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pudding dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until blended.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and half the cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon cookies into each cup.
Fill 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cookies and refrigerate. Decorate with gummy worms.

title: tomatoes with artichoke hearts
directions: Scald tomatoes to remove skins.
Scoop out centers and season them inside and out with salt, freshly ground pepper and powdered dill.
Put an artichoke heart in each tomato.
Chill.
One hour before serving, cover each tomato with a sauce made by combining mayonnaise with sour cream, curry powder, grated onion and lemon juice.
Add more curry powder if desired.
Serve very cold on bibb lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour apple cider and fruit juices into coffee pot. Place other ingredients in basket of percolator and perk. Serve hot.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix the cornstarch and 1/2 c. water to make a thin paste. Combine the remaining 1 1/2 cups water and the sugar in the top of a double boiler and bring to a boil over direct heat.
Add the cornstarch paste and cook until mixture begins to thicken; place over boiling water and continue cooking until thick and smooth, about 15 minutes.
Add a small amount of cooked mixture to egg yolks and mix back into cooked mixture.
Return to double boiler and cook 1 minute longer.
Add lemon rind, juice and butter and blend well.
Remove from heat.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes until nicely browned.

title: mexican tortilla pie
directions: Cut chicken into medium size pieces and brown in skillet.
Add green onions and cook until tender.
Add green chilies and black olives.
Add cumin and salt; fold in sour cream.

title: corned venison and cabbage
directions: Place the meat in a pan with a cover.
Cover with water, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and remove the scum from the water.
Reduce the heat and simmer for about 5 hours.
Add the vegetables and cook for an additional hour.
Serve the meat and vegetables together on a large platter.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook and mash potato while hot.
Add powdered sugar and beat well.
Add butter and moist coconut.
Cream well and spread in a buttered pan.
Melt chocolate and pour over top.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, enchilada sauce, milk and optional chili peppers.
Heat until bubbly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil together; add brown sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Cream together.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour pans (I use 4 small loaf pans).
These breads freeze well and make great gifts.

title: cheese stuffed zucchini
directions: Trim ends of zucchini.
Cook in salt water for 8 minutes. Halve lengthwise.
Scoop out center and dice.
Cook onion in 1 teaspoon of butter until tender.
Stir in zucchini plus cottage cheese, rice and egg beaten.
Mix all together; fill zucchini. Bake 25 minutes covered at 350°.
Place strip of cheese or Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake uncovered until cheese is melted.

title: piccalilli
directions: Chop the vegetables; mix well with the salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and press out as much liquid as possible.
Mix vinegar with sugar and add to the vegetables.
Put the spices in a bag and add.
Cook slowly for about 30 minutes until clear. Remove bag of spices.
Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Blend all fruits and nuts.
Allow cream cheese to soften and mix with sweetened condensed milk.
Toss in fruit mixture and stir well.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Cut chicken into chunks; fry in pan with a little bit of oil until done; drain.
Cook spinach like instructions direct and drain.
Cook noodles by instructions and drain.
Fix envelope of Alfredo sauce by instructions.
Heat container of Alfredo sauce. Put everything in pot and stir all together.
Heat until warm.

title: cole slaw
directions: In a food processor, cut cabbage, carrot, green pepper and onion.
In a small bowl, mix Miracle Whip, salt, celery seed, vinegar, sugar and milk, then mix well and serve.

title: sun country mexican minestrone soup
directions: Cut chicken in 1 x 1/2-inch cubes.
Add all remaining ingredients (except Parmesan cheese) into large pot.
Mix and bring to a boil; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until ingredients begin breaking down and flavors are well mixed. Serves 8.
Pass Parmesan cheese and fresh ground pepper.
Offer Tabasco sauce.

title: salad for lovers
directions: Drain beans and remove pork.
Add chopped eggs, crumbled bacon and dressing.
Best if made the night before or a few hours before serving.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Mix and let set a couple hours.

title: skillet date cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and dates in a skillet.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in beaten egg and vanilla.
Allow to cool for a few minutes.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut. When cool enough to handle, roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 60 walnut-sized balls.

title: chicken ambassador
directions: Sprinkle poultry seasoning on chicken.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Stir in beef consomm.
Add chicken; spoon liquid over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting every 20 minutes.
Add artichokes during last 10 minutes; just to heat. Serve with rice or noodles.
This is easy to prepare and children like it.

title: apple drop cookies
directions: Mix preceding ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: toffee nut bars
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a 10-inch square buttered casserole. Dot with butter and cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 375 degrees.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover cubed potatoes with water.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Drain 1/2 of the boiling water off, but add the same amount of fresh water back onto potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter and add dry seasonings.
Blend well and slowly add milk.
Let thicken, continuing to stir.
Add cheese.
Stir in.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Dip chips in chicken broth; layer in bottom of baking dish, then a layer of cheese, layer of onion and layer of bell pepper.
Continue layers if desired; sprinkle with excess cheese.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup with water before pouring over casserole.

title: great beer batter
directions: Mix ingredients; let stand at room temperature for 1/2 hour. Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Use chicken, fish, shrimp or vegetables.
Dip in batter; cover evenly.
Place in hot oil and fry until golden.

title: artichoke bake for dip
directions: Mix artichokes, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese; bake in Pyrex plate at 350°, until golden.
Suggestions for adding to this could be cut-up, cooked shrimp, crab meat, sweet chopped red pepper, bits of crisp bacon, etc.
Serve hot with crackers or French bread.

title: baked rice pudding custard
directions: Cook rice in salted water until tender.
Beat eggs with a spoon.
Add
sugar and milk to eggs.
Put all ingredients in a casserole
placed
in
a
pan
of water.
Bake at 400° until done. It will test done when a knife, inserted in the middle, comes out clean.

title: frango mint pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add chocolate.
Mix well. Beat in 2 eggs at a
time.
Beat
well,
then
add
peppermint
and vanilla. Pour into graham
cracker	pie shell (keep in freezer).
Can be made a day ahead of use.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix well.
Shape it out and chill.
Dip into 2 packages chocolate chips and 1/2 block paraffin wax, melted.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes and melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: good cookies
directions: Mix all at once.
Dough is very stiff.
Roll into walnut size balls and partly press down.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown. This is a good tasting cookie!!

title: fudge cake
directions: Cake:
Mix all cake ingredients 3 minutes.
Pour into a long pan.
Cook at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: gatlinburg brownies
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 4 ingredients.
Pour this over the cake mixture; sprinkle the chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With kitchen hammer or the side of a cleaver, pound out the boned breasts to 1/4-inch thick.
On each one, place a tablespoon of the chilies and a Monterey Jack cheese slice.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a baking dish. Brush with beaten egg.
Mix together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and chili powder and sprinkle over the chicken rolls, patting into place to form a crust.
Bake for about 20 minutes. Cheese inside will be melted and the crust nicely browned.
Serves 2.

title: fly off the plate rolls
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm water; set aside to dissolve.

title: ground beef andouille smoked sausage and cabbage jambalaya
directions: Place oil in 6-quart saucepan or large Dutch oven.
Add ground beef and place over high heat.
Break up meat in small chunks.
Add sausage; cook until ground beef is browned.
Stir in salt and red and black pepper; cook about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add bell pepper, onion, celery, green onions, parsley and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes; cook and stir about 2 minutes more.
Now add cabbage and do not stir.
Cover pan and cook about 25 minutes, stirring only occasionally after mixture on the bottom of the pan has browned, then scrape bottom of pan well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stock, scraping bottom of pan until sediment dissolves, then add the rest of stock.
Reduce heat to very low; add rice.
Cook 25 minutes.
Check to make sure it is not scorching.
Remove pan from heat and let sit covered 25 minutes more.
Stir well and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in powdered sugar. Beat until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature.
Heat oven to 325°. With hands, combine sausage and cheese together in a bowl.
Add Bisquick and blend thoroughly.
Roll into just smaller than golf ball-size balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes about 45.
Freezes wonderfully!

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Combine pumpkin, spice and fruit pectin.
Heat and stir over high heat until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sugar; stir until boiling.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Ladle into sterilized half pint jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust lids, then process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: texas fudge
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put Monterey Jack cheese in bottom. Cut seeds and veins out of chili peppers.
Lay on top of cheese (chop up peppers).
Put Cheddar cheese on this.
Beat eggs; pour on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scandinavian cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order given and form into little balls the size of a walnut.
Roll these in slightly beaten egg white and then in chopped walnut meats.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Make a depression in each cookie with your thumb.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Before serving, fill the depression in each cookie with currant jelly or mint jelly.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Combine Graham cracker crumb, sugar, margarine (melted). Press mixture into a 9 inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Let cool, or to save time use a pre-made graham cracker pie shell.
In a medium bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Slowly add milk and mix until smooth.
Add No-Bake Mix and mix well.
Fold Cool Whip into mix until well blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for at least an hour.
Add any kind of pie filling you like to the top.
For a 9 inch spring form pan, double the recipe for filling.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of glass pie dish.
Spread pizza sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle generously with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with tortilla chips, etc.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water with pinch of salt for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain immediately.
Reserve liquid.
Boil the eggs, peel and slice.
Butter casserole dish.
Make sauce of the soup, 2 tablespoons milk and margarine.
Use reserved liquid if necessary. Heat slowly, adding the Accent and pepper to taste.
Let bubble up. Layer broccoli, eggs and sauce.
Add almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: salsa
directions: In a small bowl, mix together the tomatoes, onion, jalapeno, and cilantro.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside for 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: wild duck(serves 4)
directions: Clean and wash ducks inside and out; dry.
Season well inside and out with salt and red pepper.
Stuff with a piece of celery, onion and bell pepper.
Brown the ducks in an open roasting pan in cooking oil.
Add water and sherry.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 3 hours or until tender.
This depends on the size of the duck.
Thicken gravy with flour that has been mixed with water. Serve hot.

title: chicken in the crock-pot
directions: Blend soup; put cream and whipping cream together.
Pour over chicken in crock-pot and let cook on low all day.

title: banana pudding
directions: Alternate layers of bananas and vanilla wafers in a bowl.
Mix sugar, flour and salt in a pan.
Add milk and warm.
Add beaten egg yolks to warm milk mixture and cook on medium heat.
Be sure to stir mixture often so that it doesn't stick.
When mixture has thickened, remove from heat and add vanilla
flavoring.
Then pour over bananas and wafers.

title: peanut butter snaps
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine.
Add honey and corn syrup. Stir in dry ingredients.
Form into a roll and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Slice and bake in 325° oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over fruit.
Sprinkle pecan on top.
Pour melted butter evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Melted butter will be absorbed.

title: nut cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder,	salt
and sugar in large bowl of electric mixer.	Add
shortening,
milk,
vanilla
and almond extract.
Beat on #3 speed	for
2 minutes.
Stop mixer, scrape beaters.
Add three eggs and
extra
yolk all at once to mixture. Beat two minutes
longer.
Scrape bowl while beating. Line well greased and lightly
floured
10-inch
tube
pan with chopped nuts and cherries.
Add batter.	Bake
in 375° oven for 50 minutes or until cake tester
comes
out
clean.
Unmold and cool.
Yields about 12 large wedges.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine Veg-All, butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush corn flakes.
Heat 1/2 stick of butter and stir into corn flakes, then press down onto casserole and bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: white peppernuts
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, lemon rind, nutmeg, cloves, salt and baking powder and 2 cups flour; mix well.
Add 1 cup flour at a time and stir by hand until too hard to stir, then work in rest of flour on board.
Take small portions of dough and form into rolls about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut in 1/2-inch lengths; roll into balls between palms.
Bake on greased cookie sheet about 8 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread 1 large container cream cheese into a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Top with 1 can Hormel chili and spread evenly.
Sprinkle cheese over chili.
Microwave approximately 4 to 6 minutes, turning several times until heated thoroughly.
Serve with white corn nachos.

title: pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart pot, place oil.
Brown roast on all sides.
Cut off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are tender.
Recover roast.
Stir flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth. Mixture boils and thickens.

title: party punch
directions: Lord, in the quiet of this morning hour I come to Thee for grace, for wisdom and power.
To view the world today through love filled eyes.
Be patient, understanding, gentle, wise.
Let me so kindly be, so full of cheer.
That all I meet may feel Thy presence ever here.
Clothe me in Thy beauty, this I pray.
Let me reveal Thee Lord through all the day.
Amen.

title: pineapple wine punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine Chablis and pineapple juice.
Peel and thinly slice kiwi.
Slice fresh strawberries.
Add kiwi and strawberries to punch and brandy, if used.
Add ice cubes.
Serve immediately.

title: parsley rice
directions: Pour rice into glass 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add water to chicken broth to make 2 cups.
Pour into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter until melted.
Pour over rice.
Cover tightly.
Bake in a 375° oven until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 30 minutes.
Stir in salt and parsley.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serve at once.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, topping out with grated cheese and Chinese noodles to cover entire casserole. (Crushed potato chips may be substituted for Chinese noodles, if desired.) Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice and the three soups together.
Spread the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch or bigger dish or pan.
Salt and pepper.
Lay on top of rice.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done and chicken is brown.
Test at 1 hour for doneness.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla, blend until smooth with cream cheese mixture.
Fold grapes into mixture.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of mixture.
Top with pecans.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In skillet, saute beef until brown; drain and season.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles according to directions; drain and separate noodles.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread a thin layer of sauce.
Top with 1/3 of the noodles.
Top with a layer of 1/3 of the Ricotta, 1/3 of the Mozzarella, 1/3 of the meat sauce and 1/3 of the Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layering 2 more times, ending with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Add margarine and sugar to Ritz crackers.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch dish but be sure and reserve some for garnishing.
Blend orange juice and Eagle Brand milk together; stir in Cool Whip. Fold in mandarin oranges.
Pour mixture over crumb crust. Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs over top.
Refrigerate or freeze until time to serve.

title: chicken dumpling pie
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients; pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish or 6-8 individual baking dishes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in a light amount of oil or chicken stock until it changes color. Drain liquid or oil and put back in pan.
Now add Ro-Tel and cook chicken until nice and tender.
The ground beef will be similar except let cook in its own juice until nice and brown.
Drain.
Add Ro-Tel and cook a few minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix
orange
juice, vinegar and oil to marinate chicken while preparing
the rest of the ingredients.
Add mayonnaise or	salad dressing to moisten.
Pecans are optional.	Wonderful!

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Cool.
Chop vegetables into salad-size pieces.
Mix noodle and Salad Supreme. Add vegetables.
Add salad dressing.
Toss and chill.

title: cheesy fruit pizza
directions: Stir together the oats, flour, 1/2 cup cheese and butter. Press onto a greased pizza pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in whipping cream, powdered sugar and vanilla; beat until thickened. Spread cream cheese mixture onto crust.
Arrange fruit pieces into attractive pattern onto pizza.
Sprinkle with additional Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes one 12-inch pizza.

title: easy baked potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 2-quart casserole dish with vegetable oil spray.
Wash, peel or leave unpeeled and cube potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Place potatoes in dish.
Cube margarine and place in dish with potatoes.
Add onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake for approximately 40 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop all vegetables and mix well.
Mix all together, except cabbage.
Add 2 teaspoons salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain off water and then mix in cabbage.
Stir up good.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Pack into jars and seal.
